18¿é 1:11 But stretch out your hand now, and touch all that he has, and he will curse you to your face."
18¿é 1:12 The LORD said to Satan, "Very well, all that he has is in your power; only do not stretch out your hand against him!" So Satan went out from the presence of the LORD.
18¿é 1:13 One day when his sons and daughters were eating and drinking wine in the eldest brother's house,
18¿é 1:14 a messenger came to Job and said, "The oxen were plowing and the donkeys were feeding beside them,
18¿é 1:15 and the Sabeans fell on them and carried them off, and killed the servants with the edge of the sword; I alone have escaped to tell you."
18¿é 1:16 While he was still speaking, another came and said, "The fire of God fell from heaven and burned up the sheep and the servants, and consumed them; I alone have escaped to tell you."
18¿é 1:17 While he was still speaking, another came and said, "The Chaldeans formed three columns, made a raid on the camels and carried them off, and killed the servants with the edge of the sword; I alone have escaped to tell you."
18¿é 1:18 While he was still speaking, another came and said, "Your sons and daughters were eating and drinking wine in their eldest brother's house,
18¿é 1:19 and suddenly a great wind came across the desert, struck the four corners of the house, and it fell on the young people, and they are dead; I alone have escaped to tell you."
18¿é 1:20 Then Job arose, tore his robe, shaved his head, and fell on the ground and worshiped.
18¿é 1:21 He said, "Naked I came from my mother's womb, and naked shall I return there; the LORD gave, and the LORD has taken away; blessed be the name of the LORD."
18¿é 1:22 In all this Job did not sin or charge God with wrong-doing.
18¿é 2:1 One day the heavenly beings came to present themselves before the LORD, and Satan also came among them to present himself before the LORD.
