18¿é 3:7 Yes, let that night be barren; let no joyful cry be heard in it.
18¿é 3:8 Let those curse it who curse the Sea, those who are skilled to rouse up Leviathan.
18¿é 3:9 Let the stars of its dawn be dark; let it hope for light, but have none; may it not see the eyelids of the morning--
