18¿é 9:6 who shakes the earth out of its place, and its pillars tremble;
18¿é 9:7 who commands the sun, and it does not rise; who seals up the stars;
18¿é 9:8 who alone stretched out the heavens and trampled the waves of the Sea;
18¿é 9:9 who made the Bear and Orion, the Pleiades and the chambers of the south;
18¿é 9:10 who does great things beyond understanding, and marvelous things without number.
18¿é 9:11 Look, he passes by me, and I do not see him; he moves on, but I do not perceive him.
