18¿é 9:21 I am blameless; I do not know myself; I loathe my life.
18¿é 9:22 It is all one; therefore I say, he destroys both the blameless and the wicked.
18¿é 9:23 When disaster brings sudden death, he mocks at the calamity of the innocent.
