18¿é 10:14 If I sin, you watch me, and do not acquit me of my iniquity.
18¿é 10:15 If I am wicked, woe to me! If I am righteous, I cannot lift up my head, for I am filled with disgrace and look upon my affliction.
18¿é 10:16 Bold as a lion you hunt me; you repeat your exploits against me.
18¿é 10:17 You renew your witnesses against me, and increase your vexation toward me; you bring fresh troops against me.
18¿é 10:18 "Why did you bring me forth from the womb? Would that I had died before any eye had seen me,
18¿é 10:19 and were as though I had not been, carried from the womb to the grave.
18¿é 10:20 Are not the days of my life few? Let me alone, that I may find a little comfort
