18¿é 12:5 Those at ease have contempt for misfortune, but it is ready for those whose feet are unstable.
18¿é 12:6 The tents of robbers are at peace, and those who provoke God are secure, who bring their god in their hands.
18¿é 12:7 "But ask the animals, and they will teach you; the birds of the air, and they will tell you;
18¿é 12:8 ask the plants of the earth, and they will teach you; and the fish of the sea will declare to you.
18¿é 12:9 Who among all these does not know that the hand of the LORD has done this?
18¿é 12:10 In his hand is the life of every living thing and the breath of every human being.
18¿é 12:11 Does not the ear test words as the palate tastes food?
18¿é 12:12 Is wisdom with the aged, and understanding in length of days?
