19½Ã 9:5 You have rebuked the nations, you have destroyed the wicked; you have blotted out their name forever and ever.
19½Ã 9:6 The enemies have vanished in everlasting ruins; their cities you have rooted out; the very memory of them has perished.
19½Ã 9:7 But the LORD sits enthroned forever, he has established his throne for judgment.
19½Ã 9:8 He judges the world with righteousness; he judges the peoples with equity.
19½Ã 9:9 The LORD is a stronghold for the oppressed, a stronghold in times of trouble.
19½Ã 9:10 And those who know your name put their trust in you, for you, O LORD, have not forsaken those who seek you.
19½Ã 9:11 Sing praises to the LORD, who dwells in Zion. Declare his deeds among the peoples.
19½Ã 9:12 For he who avenges blood is mindful of them; he does not forget the cry of the afflicted.
19½Ã 9:13 Be gracious to me, O LORD. See what I suffer from those who hate me; you are the one who lifts me up from the gates of death,
19½Ã 9:14 so that I may recount all your praises, and, in the gates of daughter Zion, rejoice in your deliverance.
19½Ã 9:15 The nations have sunk in the pit that they made; in the net that they hid has their own foot been caught.
19½Ã 9:16 The LORD has made himself known, he has executed judgment; the wicked are snared in the work of their own hands. Higgaion. Selah
19½Ã 9:17 The wicked shall depart to Sheol, all the nations that forget God.
19½Ã 9:18 For the needy shall not always be forgotten, nor the hope of the poor perish forever.
19½Ã 9:19 Rise up, O LORD! Do not let mortals prevail; let the nations be judged before you.
19½Ã 9:20 Put them in fear, O LORD; let the nations know that they are only human. Selah
19½Ã 10:1 Why, O LORD, do you stand far off? Why do you hide yourself in times of trouble?
19½Ã 10:2 In arrogance the wicked persecute the poor--let them be caught in the schemes they have devised.
19½Ã 10:3 For the wicked boast of the desires of their heart, those greedy for gain curse and renounce the LORD.
19½Ã 10:4 In the pride of their countenance the wicked say, "God will not seek it out"; all their thoughts are, "There is no God."
19½Ã 10:5 Their ways prosper at all times; your judgments are on high, out of their sight; as for their foes, they scoff at them.
19½Ã 10:6 They think in their heart, "We shall not be moved; throughout all generations we shall not meet adversity."
19½Ã 10:7 Their mouths are filled with cursing and deceit and oppression; under their tongues are mischief and iniquity.
19½Ã 10:8 They sit in ambush in the villages; in hiding places they murder the innocent. Their eyes stealthily watch for the helpless;
19½Ã 10:9 they lurk in secret like a lion in its covert; they lurk that they may seize the poor; they seize the poor and drag them off in their net.
19½Ã 10:10 They stoop, they crouch, and the helpless fall by their might.
19½Ã 10:11 They think in their heart, "God has forgotten, he has hidden his face, he will never see it."
19½Ã 10:12 Rise up, O LORD; O God, lift up your hand; do not forget the oppressed.
19½Ã 10:13 Why do the wicked renounce God, and say in their hearts, "You will not call us to account"?
19½Ã 10:14 But you do see! Indeed you note trouble and grief, that you may take it into your hands; the helpless commit themselves to you; you have been the helper of the orphan.
19½Ã 10:15 Break the arm of the wicked and evildoers; seek out their wickedness until you find none.
19½Ã 10:16 The LORD is king forever and ever; the nations shall perish from his land.
19½Ã 10:17 O LORD, you will hear the desire of the meek; you will strengthen their heart, you will incline your ear
19½Ã 10:18 to do justice for the orphan and the oppressed, so that those from earth may strike terror no more.
19½Ã 11:1 To the leader. Of David. In the LORD I take refuge; how can you say to me, "Flee like a bird to the mountains;
19½Ã 11:2 for look, the wicked bend the bow, they have fitted their arrow to the string, to shoot in the dark at the upright in heart.
19½Ã 11:3 If the foundations are destroyed, what can the righteous do?"
19½Ã 11:4 The LORD is in his holy temple; the LORD's throne is in heaven. His eyes behold, his gaze examines humankind.
19½Ã 11:5 The LORD tests the righteous and the wicked, and his soul hates the lover of violence.
19½Ã 11:6 On the wicked he will rain coals of fire and sulfur; a scorching wind shall be the portion of their cup.
19½Ã 11:7 For the LORD is righteous; he loves righteous deeds; the upright shall behold his face.
19½Ã 12:1 To the leader: according to The Sheminith. A Psalm of David. Help, O LORD, for there is no longer anyone who is godly; the faithful have disappeared from humankind.
19½Ã 12:2 They utter lies to each other; with flattering lips and a double heart they speak.
19½Ã 12:3 May the LORD cut off all flattering lips, the tongue that makes great boasts,
19½Ã 12:4 those who say, "With our tongues we will prevail; our lips are our own--who is our master?"
19½Ã 12:5 "Because the poor are despoiled, because the needy groan, I will now rise up," says the LORD; "I will place them in the safety for which they long."
19½Ã 12:6 The promises of the LORD are promises that are pure, silver refined in a furnace on the ground, purified seven times.
19½Ã 12:7 You, O LORD, will protect us; you will guard us from this generation forever.
19½Ã 12:8 On every side the wicked prowl, as vileness is exalted among humankind.
19½Ã 13:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. How long, O LORD? Will you forget me forever? How long will you hide your face from me?
19½Ã 13:2 How long must I bear pain in my soul, and have sorrow in my heart all day long? How long shall my enemy be exalted over me?
19½Ã 13:3 Consider and answer me, O LORD my God! Give light to my eyes, or I will sleep the sleep of death,
19½Ã 13:4 and my enemy will say, "I have prevailed"; my foes will rejoice because I am shaken.
19½Ã 13:5 But I trusted in your steadfast love; my heart shall rejoice in your salvation.
19½Ã 13:6 I will sing to the LORD, because he has dealt bountifully with me.
19½Ã 14:1 To the leader. Of David. Fools say in their hearts, "There is no God." They are corrupt, they do abominable deeds; there is no one who does good.
19½Ã 14:2 The LORD looks down from heaven on humankind to see if there are any who are wise, who seek after God.
19½Ã 14:3 They have all gone astray, they are all alike perverse; there is no one who does good, no, not one.
19½Ã 14:4 Have they no knowledge, all the evildoers who eat up my people as they eat bread, and do not call upon the LORD?
19½Ã 14:5 There they shall be in great terror, for God is with the company of the righteous.
19½Ã 14:6 You would confound the plans of the poor, but the LORD is their refuge.
19½Ã 14:7 O that deliverance for Israel would come from Zion! When the LORD restores the fortunes of his people, Jacob will rejoice; Israel will be glad.
19½Ã 15:1 A Psalm of David. O LORD, who may abide in your tent? Who may dwell on your holy hill?
19½Ã 15:2 Those who walk blamelessly, and do what is right, and speak the truth from their heart;
19½Ã 15:3 who do not slander with their tongue, and do no evil to their friends, nor take up a reproach against their neighbors;
19½Ã 15:4 in whose eyes the wicked are despised, but who honor those who fear the LORD; who stand by their oath even to their hurt;
19½Ã 15:5 who do not lend money at interest, and do not take a bribe against the innocent. Those who do these things shall never be moved.
19½Ã 16:1 A Miktam of David. Protect me, O God, for in you I take refuge.
19½Ã 16:2 I say to the LORD, "You are my Lord; I have no good apart from you."
19½Ã 16:3 As for the holy ones in the land, they are the noble, in whom is all my delight.
19½Ã 16:4 Those who choose another god multiply their sorrows; their drink offerings of blood I will not pour out or take their names upon my lips.
19½Ã 16:5 The LORD is my chosen portion and my cup; you hold my lot.
19½Ã 16:6 The boundary lines have fallen for me in pleasant places; I have a goodly heritage.
19½Ã 16:7 I bless the LORD who gives me counsel; in the night also my heart instructs me.
19½Ã 16:8 I keep the LORD always before me; because he is at my right hand, I shall not be moved.
19½Ã 16:9 Therefore my heart is glad, and my soul rejoices; my body also rests secure.
19½Ã 16:10 For you do not give me up to Sheol, or let your faithful one see the Pit.
19½Ã 16:11 You show me the path of life. In your presence there is fullness of joy; in your right hand are pleasures forevermore.
19½Ã 17:1 A Prayer of David. Hear a just cause, O LORD; attend to my cry; give ear to my prayer from lips free of deceit.
19½Ã 17:2 From you let my vindication come; let your eyes see the right.
19½Ã 17:3 If you try my heart, if you visit me by night, if you test me, you will find no wickedness in me; my mouth does not transgress.
19½Ã 17:4 As for what others do, by the word of your lips I have avoided the ways of the violent.
19½Ã 17:5 My steps have held fast to your paths; my feet have not slipped.
19½Ã 17:6 I call upon you, for you will answer me, O God; incline your ear to me, hear my words.
19½Ã 17:7 Wondrously show your steadfast love, O savior of those who seek refuge from their adversaries at your right hand.
19½Ã 17:8 Guard me as the apple of the eye; hide me in the shadow of your wings,
19½Ã 17:9 from the wicked who despoil me, my deadly enemies who surround me.
19½Ã 17:10 They close their hearts to pity; with their mouths they speak arrogantly.
19½Ã 17:11 They track me down; now they surround me; they set their eyes to cast me to the ground.
19½Ã 17:12 They are like a lion eager to tear, like a young lion lurking in ambush.
19½Ã 17:13 Rise up, O LORD, confront them, overthrow them! By your sword deliver my life from the wicked,
19½Ã 17:14 from mortals--by your hand, O LORD--from mortals whose portion in life is in this world. May their bellies be filled with what you have stored up for them; may their children have more than enough; may they leave something over to their little ones.
19½Ã 17:15 As for me, I shall behold your face in righteousness; when I awake I shall be satisfied, beholding your likeness.
19½Ã 18:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David the servant of the LORD, who addressed the words of this song to the LORD on the day when the LORD delivered him from the hand of all his enemies, and from the hand of Saul. He said: I love you, O LORD, my strength.
19½Ã 18:2 The LORD is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer, my God, my rock in whom I take refuge, my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold.
19½Ã 18:3 I call upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised, so I shall be saved from my enemies.
19½Ã 18:4 The cords of death encompassed me; the torrents of perdition assailed me;
19½Ã 18:5 the cords of Sheol entangled me; the snares of death confronted me.
19½Ã 18:6 In my distress I called upon the LORD; to my God I cried for help. From his temple he heard my voice, and my cry to him reached his ears.
19½Ã 18:7 Then the earth reeled and rocked; the foundations also of the mountains trembled and quaked, because he was angry.
19½Ã 18:8 Smoke went up from his nostrils, and devouring fire from his mouth; glowing coals flamed forth from him.
19½Ã 18:9 He bowed the heavens, and came down; thick darkness was under his feet.
19½Ã 18:10 He rode on a cherub, and flew; he came swiftly upon the wings of the wind.
19½Ã 18:11 He made darkness his covering around him, his canopy thick clouds dark with water.
19½Ã 18:12 Out of the brightness before him there broke through his clouds hailstones and coals of fire.
19½Ã 18:13 The LORD also thundered in the heavens, and the Most High uttered his voice.
19½Ã 18:14 And he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; he flashed forth lightnings, and routed them.
19½Ã 18:15 Then the channels of the sea were seen, and the foundations of the world were laid bare at your rebuke, O LORD, at the blast of the breath of your nostrils.
19½Ã 18:16 He reached down from on high, he took me; he drew me out of mighty waters.
19½Ã 18:17 He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from those who hated me; for they were too mighty for me.
19½Ã 18:18 They confronted me in the day of my calamity; but the LORD was my support.
19½Ã 18:19 He brought me out into a broad place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.
19½Ã 18:20 The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands he recompensed me.
19½Ã 18:21 For I have kept the ways of the LORD, and have not wickedly departed from my God.
19½Ã 18:22 For all his ordinances were before me, and his statutes I did not put away from me.
19½Ã 18:23 I was blameless before him, and I kept myself from guilt.
19½Ã 18:24 Therefore the LORD has recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his sight.
19½Ã 18:25 With the loyal you show yourself loyal; with the blameless you show yourself blameless;
19½Ã 18:26 with the pure you show yourself pure; and with the crooked you show yourself perverse.
19½Ã 18:27 For you deliver a humble people, but the haughty eyes you bring down.
19½Ã 18:28 It is you who light my lamp; the LORD, my God, lights up my darkness.
19½Ã 18:29 By you I can crush a troop, and by my God I can leap over a wall.
19½Ã 18:30 This God--his way is perfect; the promise of the LORD proves true; he is a shield for all who take refuge in him.
19½Ã 18:31 For who is God except the LORD? And who is a rock besides our God?--
19½Ã 18:32 the God who girded me with strength, and made my way safe.
19½Ã 18:33 He made my feet like the feet of a deer, and set me secure on the heights.
19½Ã 18:34 He trains my hands for war, so that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.
19½Ã 18:35 You have given me the shield of your salvation, and your right hand has supported me; your help has made me great.
19½Ã 18:36 You gave me a wide place for my steps under me, and my feet did not slip.
19½Ã 18:37 I pursued my enemies and overtook them; and did not turn back until they were consumed.
19½Ã 18:38 I struck them down, so that they were not able to rise; they fell under my feet.
19½Ã 18:39 For you girded me with strength for the battle; you made my assailants sink under me.
19½Ã 18:40 You made my enemies turn their backs to me, and those who hated me I destroyed.
19½Ã 18:41 They cried for help, but there was no one to save them; they cried to the LORD, but he did not answer them.
19½Ã 18:42 I beat them fine, like dust before the wind; I cast them out like the mire of the streets.
19½Ã 18:43 You delivered me from strife with the peoples; You made me head of the nations; people whom I had not known served me.
19½Ã 18:44 As soon as they heard of me they obeyed me; foreigners came cringing to me.
19½Ã 18:45 Foreigners lost heart, and came trembling out of their strongholds.
19½Ã 18:46 The LORD lives! Blessed be my rock, and exalted be the God of my salvation,
19½Ã 18:47 the God who gave me vengeance and subdued peoples under me;
19½Ã 18:48 who delivered me from my enemies; indeed, you exalted me above my adversaries; you delivered me from the violent.
19½Ã 18:49 For this I will extol you, O LORD, among the nations, and sing praises to your name.
19½Ã 18:50 Great triumphs he gives to his king, and shows steadfast love to his anointed, to David and his descendants forever.
19½Ã 19:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. The heavens are telling the glory of God; and the firmament proclaims his handiwork.
19½Ã 19:2 Day to day pours forth speech, and night to night declares knowledge.
19½Ã 19:3 There is no speech, nor are there words; their voice is not heard;
19½Ã 19:4 yet their voice goes out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world. In the heavens he has set a tent for the sun,
19½Ã 19:5 which comes out like a bridegroom from his wedding canopy, and like a strong man runs its course with joy.
19½Ã 19:6 Its rising is from the end of the heavens, and its circuit to the end of them; and nothing is hid from its heat.
19½Ã 19:7 The law of the LORD is perfect, reviving the soul; the decrees of the LORD are sure, making wise the simple;
19½Ã 19:8 the precepts of the LORD are right, rejoicing the heart; the commandment of the LORD is clear, enlightening the eyes;
19½Ã 19:9 the fear of the LORD is pure, enduring forever; the ordinances of the LORD are true and righteous altogether.
19½Ã 19:10 More to be desired are they than gold, even much fine gold; sweeter also than honey, and drippings of the honeycomb.
19½Ã 19:11 Moreover by them is your servant warned; in keeping them there is great reward.
19½Ã 19:12 But who can detect their errors? Clear me from hidden faults.
19½Ã 19:13 Keep back your servant also from the insolent; do not let them have dominion over me. Then I shall be blameless, and innocent of great transgression.
19½Ã 19:14 Let the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart be acceptable to you, O LORD, my rock and my redeemer.
19½Ã 20:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. The LORD answer you in the day of trouble! The name of the God of Jacob protect you!
19½Ã 20:2 May he send you help from the sanctuary, and give you support from Zion.
19½Ã 20:3 May he remember all your offerings, and regard with favor your burnt sacrifices. Selah
19½Ã 20:4 May he grant you your heart's desire, and fulfill all your plans.
19½Ã 20:5 May we shout for joy over your victory, and in the name of our God set up our banners. May the LORD fulfill all your petitions.
19½Ã 20:6 Now I know that the LORD will help his anointed; he will answer him from his holy heaven with mighty victories by his right hand.
19½Ã 20:7 Some take pride in chariots, and some in horses, but our pride is in the name of the LORD our God.
19½Ã 20:8 They will collapse and fall, but we shall rise and stand upright.
19½Ã 20:9 Give victory to the king, O LORD; answer us when we call.
19½Ã 21:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. In your strength the king rejoices, O LORD, and in your help how greatly he exults!
19½Ã 21:2 You have given him his heart's desire, and have not withheld the request of his lips. Selah
19½Ã 21:3 For you meet him with rich blessings; you set a crown of fine gold on his head.
19½Ã 21:4 He asked you for life; you gave it to him--length of days forever and ever.
19½Ã 21:5 His glory is great through your help; splendor and majesty you bestow on him.
19½Ã 21:6 You bestow on him blessings forever; you make him glad with the joy of your presence.
19½Ã 21:7 For the king trusts in the LORD, and through the steadfast love of the Most High he shall not be moved.
19½Ã 21:8 Your hand will find out all your enemies; your right hand will find out those who hate you.
19½Ã 21:9 You will make them like a fiery furnace when you appear. The LORD will swallow them up in his wrath, and fire will consume them.
19½Ã 21:10 You will destroy their offspring from the earth, and their children from among humankind.
19½Ã 21:11 If they plan evil against you, if they devise mischief, they will not succeed.
19½Ã 21:12 For you will put them to flight; you will aim at their faces with your bows.
19½Ã 21:13 Be exalted, O LORD, in your strength! We will sing and praise your power.
19½Ã 22:1 To the leader: according to The Deer of the Dawn. A Psalm of David. My God, my God, why have you forsaken me? Why are you so far from helping me, from the words of my groaning?
19½Ã 22:2 O my God, I cry by day, but you do not answer; and by night, but find no rest.
19½Ã 22:3 Yet you are holy, enthroned on the praises of Israel.
19½Ã 22:4 In you our ancestors trusted; they trusted, and you delivered them.
19½Ã 22:5 To you they cried, and were saved; in you they trusted, and were not put to shame.
19½Ã 22:6 But I am a worm, and not human; scorned by others, and despised by the people.
19½Ã 22:7 All who see me mock at me; they make mouths at me, they shake their heads;
19½Ã 22:8 "Commit your cause to the LORD; let him deliver--let him rescue the one in whom he delights!"
19½Ã 22:9 Yet it was you who took me from the womb; you kept me safe on my mother's breast.
19½Ã 22:10 On you I was cast from my birth, and since my mother bore me you have been my God.
19½Ã 22:11 Do not be far from me, for trouble is near and there is no one to help.
19½Ã 22:12 Many bulls encircle me, strong bulls of Bashan surround me;
19½Ã 22:13 they open wide their mouths at me, like a ravening and roaring lion.
19½Ã 22:14 I am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint; my heart is like wax; it is melted within my breast;
19½Ã 22:15 my mouth is dried up like a potsherd, and my tongue sticks to my jaws; you lay me in the dust of death.
19½Ã 22:16 For dogs are all around me; a company of evildoers encircles me. My hands and feet have shriveled;
19½Ã 22:17 I can count all my bones. They stare and gloat over me;
19½Ã 22:18 they divide my clothes among themselves, and for my clothing they cast lots.
19½Ã 22:19 But you, O LORD, do not be far away! O my help, come quickly to my aid!
19½Ã 22:20 Deliver my soul from the sword, my life from the power of the dog!
19½Ã 22:21 Save me from the mouth of the lion! From the horns of the wild oxen you have rescued me.
19½Ã 22:22 I will tell of your name to my brothers and sisters; in the midst of the congregation I will praise you:
19½Ã 22:23 You who fear the LORD, praise him! All you offspring of Jacob, glorify him; stand in awe of him, all you offspring of Israel!
19½Ã 22:24 For he did not despise or abhor the affliction of the afflicted; he did not hide his face from me, but heard when I cried to him.
19½Ã 22:25 From you comes my praise in the great congregation; my vows I will pay before those who fear him.
19½Ã 22:26 The poor shall eat and be satisfied; those who seek him shall praise the LORD. May your hearts live forever!
19½Ã 22:27 All the ends of the earth shall remember and turn to the LORD; and all the families of the nations shall worship before him.
19½Ã 22:28 For dominion belongs to the LORD, and he rules over the nations.
19½Ã 22:29 To him, indeed, shall all who sleep in the earth bow down; before him shall bow all who go down to the dust, and I shall live for him.
19½Ã 22:30 Posterity will serve him; future generations will be told about the Lord,
19½Ã 22:31 and proclaim his deliverance to a people yet unborn, saying that he has done it.
19½Ã 23:1 A Psalm of David. The LORD is my shepherd, I shall not want.
19½Ã 23:2 He makes me lie down in green pastures; he leads me beside still waters;
19½Ã 23:3 he restores my soul. He leads me in right paths for his name's sake.
19½Ã 23:4 Even though I walk through the darkest valley, I fear no evil; for you are with me; your rod and your staff--they comfort me.
19½Ã 23:5 You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies; you anoint my head with oil; my cup overflows.
19½Ã 23:6 Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life, and I shall dwell in the house of the LORD my whole life long.
19½Ã 24:1 Of David. A Psalm. The earth is the LORD's and all that is in it, the world, and those who live in it;
19½Ã 24:2 for he has founded it on the seas, and established it on the rivers.
19½Ã 24:3 Who shall ascend the hill of the LORD? And who shall stand in his holy place?
19½Ã 24:4 Those who have clean hands and pure hearts, who do not lift up their souls to what is false, and do not swear deceitfully.
19½Ã 24:5 They will receive blessing from the LORD, and vindication from the God of their salvation.
19½Ã 24:6 Such is the company of those who seek him, who seek the face of the God of Jacob. Selah
19½Ã 24:7 Lift up your heads, O gates! and be lifted up, O ancient doors! that the King of glory may come in.
19½Ã 24:8 Who is the King of glory? The LORD, strong and mighty, the LORD, mighty in battle.
19½Ã 24:9 Lift up your heads, O gates! and be lifted up, O ancient doors! that the King of glory may come in.
19½Ã 24:10 Who is this King of glory? The LORD of hosts, he is the King of glory. Selah
19½Ã 25:1 Of David. To you, O LORD, I lift up my soul.
19½Ã 25:2 O my God, in you I trust; do not let me be put to shame; do not let my enemies exult over me.
19½Ã 25:3 Do not let those who wait for you be put to shame; let them be ashamed who are wantonly treacherous.
