19½Ã 25:5 Lead me in your truth, and teach me, for you are the God of my salvation; for you I wait all day long.
19½Ã 25:6 Be mindful of your mercy, O LORD, and of your steadfast love, for they have been from of old.
19½Ã 25:7 Do not remember the sins of my youth or my transgressions; according to your steadfast love remember me, for your goodness' sake, O LORD!
19½Ã 25:8 Good and upright is the LORD; therefore he instructs sinners in the way.
19½Ã 25:9 He leads the humble in what is right, and teaches the humble his way.
19½Ã 25:10 All the paths of the LORD are steadfast love and faithfulness, for those who keep his covenant and his decrees.
19½Ã 25:11 For your name's sake, O LORD, pardon my guilt, for it is great.
19½Ã 25:12 Who are they that fear the LORD? He will teach them the way that they should choose.
19½Ã 25:13 They will abide in prosperity, and their children shall possess the land.
19½Ã 25:14 The friendship of the LORD is for those who fear him, and he makes his covenant known to them.
19½Ã 25:15 My eyes are ever toward the LORD, for he will pluck my feet out of the net.
19½Ã 25:16 Turn to me and be gracious to me, for I am lonely and afflicted.
19½Ã 25:17 Relieve the troubles of my heart, and bring me out of my distress.
19½Ã 25:18 Consider my affliction and my trouble, and forgive all my sins.
19½Ã 25:19 Consider how many are my foes, and with what violent hatred they hate me.
19½Ã 25:20 O guard my life, and deliver me; do not let me be put to shame, for I take refuge in you.
19½Ã 25:21 May integrity and uprightness preserve me, for I wait for you.
19½Ã 25:22 Redeem Israel, O God, out of all its troubles.
19½Ã 26:1 Of David. Vindicate me, O LORD, for I have walked in my integrity, and I have trusted in the LORD without wavering.
19½Ã 26:2 Prove me, O LORD, and try me; test my heart and mind.
19½Ã 26:3 For your steadfast love is before my eyes, and I walk in faithfulness to you.
19½Ã 26:4 I do not sit with the worthless, nor do I consort with hypocrites;
19½Ã 26:5 I hate the company of evildoers, and will not sit with the wicked.
19½Ã 26:6 I wash my hands in innocence, and go around your altar, O LORD,
19½Ã 26:7 singing aloud a song of thanksgiving, and telling all your wondrous deeds.
19½Ã 26:8 O LORD, I love the house in which you dwell, and the place where your glory abides.
19½Ã 26:9 Do not sweep me away with sinners, nor my life with the bloodthirsty,
19½Ã 26:10 those in whose hands are evil devices, and whose right hands are full of bribes.
19½Ã 26:11 But as for me, I walk in my integrity; redeem me, and be gracious to me.
19½Ã 26:12 My foot stands on level ground; in the great congregation I will bless the LORD.
19½Ã 27:1 Of David. The LORD is my light and my salvation; whom shall I fear? The LORD is the stronghold of my life; of whom shall I be afraid?
19½Ã 27:2 When evildoers assail me to devour my flesh--my adversaries and foes--they shall stumble and fall.
19½Ã 27:3 Though an army encamp against me, my heart shall not fear; though war rise up against me, yet I will be confident.
19½Ã 27:4 One thing I asked of the LORD, that will I seek after: to live in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, to behold the beauty of the LORD, and to inquire in his temple.
19½Ã 27:5 For he will hide me in his shelter in the day of trouble; he will conceal me under the cover of his tent; he will set me high on a rock.
19½Ã 27:6 Now my head is lifted up above my enemies all around me, and I will offer in his tent sacrifices with shouts of joy; I will sing and make melody to the LORD.
19½Ã 27:7 Hear, O LORD, when I cry aloud, be gracious to me and answer me!
19½Ã 27:8 "Come," my heart says, "seek his face!" Your face, LORD, do I seek.
19½Ã 27:9 Do not hide your face from me. Do not turn your servant away in anger, you who have been my help. Do not cast me off, do not forsake me, O God of my salvation!
19½Ã 27:10 If my father and mother forsake me, the LORD will take me up.
19½Ã 27:11 Teach me your way, O LORD, and lead me on a level path because of my enemies.
19½Ã 27:12 Do not give me up to the will of my adversaries, for false witnesses have risen against me, and they are breathing out violence.
19½Ã 27:13 I believe that I shall see the goodness of the LORD in the land of the living.
19½Ã 27:14 Wait for the LORD; be strong, and let your heart take courage; wait for the LORD!
19½Ã 28:1 Of David. To you, O LORD, I call; my rock, do not refuse to hear me, for if you are silent to me, I shall be like those who go down to the Pit.
19½Ã 28:2 Hear the voice of my supplication, as I cry to you for help, as I lift up my hands toward your most holy sanctuary.
19½Ã 28:3 Do not drag me away with the wicked, with those who are workers of evil, who speak peace with their neighbors, while mischief is in their hearts.
19½Ã 28:4 Repay them according to their work, and according to the evil of their deeds; repay them according to the work of their hands; render them their due reward.
19½Ã 28:5 Because they do not regard the works of the LORD, or the work of his hands, he will break them down and build them up no more.
19½Ã 28:6 Blessed be the LORD, for he has heard the sound of my pleadings.
19½Ã 28:7 The LORD is my strength and my shield; in him my heart trusts; so I am helped, and my heart exults, and with my song I give thanks to him.
19½Ã 28:8 The LORD is the strength of his people; he is the saving refuge of his anointed.
19½Ã 28:9 O save your people, and bless your heritage; be their shepherd, and carry them forever.
19½Ã 29:1 A Psalm of David. Ascribe to the LORD, O heavenly beings, ascribe to the LORD glory and strength.
19½Ã 29:2 Ascribe to the LORD the glory of his name; worship the LORD in holy splendor.
19½Ã 29:3 The voice of the LORD is over the waters; the God of glory thunders, the LORD, over mighty waters.
19½Ã 29:4 The voice of the LORD is powerful; the voice of the LORD is full of majesty.
19½Ã 29:5 The voice of the LORD breaks the cedars; the LORD breaks the cedars of Lebanon.
19½Ã 29:6 He makes Lebanon skip like a calf, and Sirion like a young wild ox.
19½Ã 29:7 The voice of the LORD flashes forth flames of fire.
19½Ã 29:8 The voice of the LORD shakes the wilderness; the LORD shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.
19½Ã 29:9 The voice of the LORD causes the oaks to whirl, and strips the forest bare; and in his temple all say, "Glory!"
19½Ã 29:10 The LORD sits enthroned over the flood; the LORD sits enthroned as king forever.
19½Ã 29:11 May the LORD give strength to his people! May the LORD bless his people with peace!
19½Ã 30:1 A Psalm. A Song at the dedication of the temple. Of David. I will extol you, O LORD, for you have drawn me up, and did not let my foes rejoice over me.
19½Ã 30:2 O LORD my God, I cried to you for help, and you have healed me.
19½Ã 30:3 O LORD, you brought up my soul from Sheol, restored me to life from among those gone down to the Pit.
19½Ã 30:4 Sing praises to the LORD, O you his faithful ones, and give thanks to his holy name.
19½Ã 30:5 For his anger is but for a moment; his favor is for a lifetime. Weeping may linger for the night, but joy comes with the morning.
19½Ã 30:6 As for me, I said in my prosperity, "I shall never be moved."
19½Ã 30:7 By your favor, O LORD, you had established me as a strong mountain; you hid your face; I was dismayed.
19½Ã 30:8 To you, O LORD, I cried, and to the LORD I made supplication:
19½Ã 30:9 "What profit is there in my death, if I go down to the Pit? Will the dust praise you? Will it tell of your faithfulness?
19½Ã 30:10 Hear, O LORD, and be gracious to me! O LORD, be my helper!"
19½Ã 30:11 You have turned my mourning into dancing; you have taken off my sackcloth and clothed me with joy,
19½Ã 30:12 so that my soul may praise you and not be silent. O LORD my God, I will give thanks to you forever.
19½Ã 31:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. In you, O LORD, I seek refuge; do not let me ever be put to shame; in your righteousness deliver me.
19½Ã 31:2 Incline your ear to me; rescue me speedily. Be a rock of refuge for me, a strong fortress to save me.
19½Ã 31:3 You are indeed my rock and my fortress; for your name's sake lead me and guide me,
19½Ã 31:4 take me out of the net that is hidden for me, for you are my refuge.
19½Ã 31:5 Into your hand I commit my spirit; you have redeemed me, O LORD, faithful God.
19½Ã 31:6 You hate those who pay regard to worthless idols, but I trust in the LORD.
19½Ã 31:7 I will exult and rejoice in your steadfast love, because you have seen my affliction; you have taken heed of my adversities,
19½Ã 31:8 and have not delivered me into the hand of the enemy; you have set my feet in a broad place.
19½Ã 31:9 Be gracious to me, O LORD, for I am in distress; my eye wastes away from grief, my soul and body also.
19½Ã 31:10 For my life is spent with sorrow, and my years with sighing; my strength fails because of my misery, and my bones waste away.
19½Ã 31:11 I am the scorn of all my adversaries, a horror to my neighbors, an object of dread to my acquaintances; those who see me in the street flee from me.
19½Ã 31:12 I have passed out of mind like one who is dead; I have become like a broken vessel.
19½Ã 31:13 For I hear the whispering of many--terror all around!--as they scheme together against me, as they plot to take my life.
19½Ã 31:14 But I trust in you, O LORD; I say, "You are my God."
19½Ã 31:15 My times are in your hand; deliver me from the hand of my enemies and persecutors.
19½Ã 31:16 Let your face shine upon your servant; save me in your steadfast love.
19½Ã 31:17 Do not let me be put to shame, O LORD, for I call on you; let the wicked be put to shame; let them go dumbfounded to Sheol.
19½Ã 31:18 Let the lying lips be stilled that speak insolently against the righteous with pride and contempt.
19½Ã 31:19 O how abundant is your goodness that you have laid up for those who fear you, and accomplished for those who take refuge in you, in the sight of everyone!
19½Ã 31:20 In the shelter of your presence you hide them from human plots; you hold them safe under your shelter from contentious tongues.
19½Ã 31:21 Blessed be the LORD, for he has wondrously shown his steadfast love to me when I was beset as in a besieged city.
19½Ã 31:22 I had said in my alarm, "I am driven far from your sight." But you heard my supplications when I cried out to you for help.
19½Ã 31:23 Love the LORD, all you his saints. The LORD preserves the faithful, but abundantly repays the one who acts haughtily.
19½Ã 31:24 Be strong, and let your heart take courage, all you who wait for the LORD.
19½Ã 32:1 Of David. A Maskil. Happy are those whose transgression is forgiven, whose sin is covered.
19½Ã 32:2 Happy are those to whom the LORD imputes no iniquity, and in whose spirit there is no deceit.
19½Ã 32:3 While I kept silence, my body wasted away through my groaning all day long.
19½Ã 32:4 For day and night your hand was heavy upon me; my strength was dried up as by the heat of summer. Selah
19½Ã 32:5 Then I acknowledged my sin to you, and I did not hide my iniquity; I said, "I will confess my transgressions to the LORD," and you forgave the guilt of my sin. Selah
19½Ã 32:6 Therefore let all who are faithful offer prayer to you; at a time of distress, the rush of mighty waters shall not reach them.
19½Ã 32:7 You are a hiding place for me; you preserve me from trouble; you surround me with glad cries of deliverance. Selah
19½Ã 32:8 I will instruct you and teach you the way you should go; I will counsel you with my eye upon you.
19½Ã 32:9 Do not be like a horse or a mule, without understanding, whose temper must be curbed with bit and bridle, else it will not stay near you.
19½Ã 32:10 Many are the torments of the wicked, but steadfast love surrounds those who trust in the LORD.
19½Ã 32:11 Be glad in the LORD and rejoice, O righteous, and shout for joy, all you upright in heart.
19½Ã 33:1 Rejoice in the LORD, O you righteous. Praise befits the upright.
19½Ã 33:2 Praise the LORD with the lyre; make melody to him with the harp of ten strings.
19½Ã 33:3 Sing to him a new song; play skillfully on the strings, with loud shouts.
19½Ã 33:4 For the word of the LORD is upright, and all his work is done in faithfulness.
19½Ã 33:5 He loves righteousness and justice; the earth is full of the steadfast love of the LORD.
19½Ã 33:6 By the word of the LORD the heavens were made, and all their host by the breath of his mouth.
19½Ã 33:7 He gathered the waters of the sea as in a bottle; he put the deeps in storehouses.
19½Ã 33:8 Let all the earth fear the LORD; let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.
19½Ã 33:9 For he spoke, and it came to be; he commanded, and it stood firm.
19½Ã 33:10 The LORD brings the counsel of the nations to nothing; he frustrates the plans of the peoples.
19½Ã 33:11 The counsel of the LORD stands forever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations.
19½Ã 33:12 Happy is the nation whose God is the LORD, the people whom he has chosen as his heritage.
19½Ã 33:13 The LORD looks down from heaven; he sees all humankind.
19½Ã 33:14 From where he sits enthroned he watches all the inhabitants of the earth--
19½Ã 33:15 he who fashions the hearts of them all, and observes all their deeds.
19½Ã 33:16 A king is not saved by his great army; a warrior is not delivered by his great strength.
19½Ã 33:17 The war horse is a vain hope for victory, and by its great might it cannot save.
19½Ã 33:18 Truly the eye of the LORD is on those who fear him, on those who hope in his steadfast love,
19½Ã 33:19 to deliver their soul from death, and to keep them alive in famine.
19½Ã 33:20 Our soul waits for the LORD; he is our help and shield.
19½Ã 33:21 Our heart is glad in him, because we trust in his holy name.
19½Ã 33:22 Let your steadfast love, O LORD, be upon us, even as we hope in you.
19½Ã 34:1 Of David, when he feigned madness before Abimelech, so that he drove him out, and he went away. I will bless the LORD at all times; his praise shall continually be in my mouth.
19½Ã 34:2 My soul makes its boast in the LORD; let the humble hear and be glad.
19½Ã 34:3 O magnify the LORD with me, and let us exalt his name together.
19½Ã 34:4 I sought the LORD, and he answered me, and delivered me from all my fears.
19½Ã 34:5 Look to him, and be radiant; so your faces shall never be ashamed.
19½Ã 34:6 This poor soul cried, and was heard by the LORD, and was saved from every trouble.
19½Ã 34:7 The angel of the LORD encamps around those who fear him, and delivers them.
19½Ã 34:8 O taste and see that the LORD is good; happy are those who take refuge in him.
19½Ã 34:9 O fear the LORD, you his holy ones, for those who fear him have no want.
19½Ã 34:10 The young lions suffer want and hunger, but those who seek the LORD lack no good thing.
19½Ã 34:11 Come, O children, listen to me; I will teach you the fear of the LORD.
19½Ã 34:12 Which of you desires life, and covets many days to enjoy good?
19½Ã 34:13 Keep your tongue from evil, and your lips from speaking deceit.
19½Ã 34:14 Depart from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it.
19½Ã 34:15 The eyes of the LORD are on the righteous, and his ears are open to their cry.
19½Ã 34:16 The face of the LORD is against evildoers, to cut off the remembrance of them from the earth.
19½Ã 34:17 When the righteous cry for help, the LORD hears, and rescues them from all their troubles.
19½Ã 34:18 The LORD is near to the brokenhearted, and saves the crushed in spirit.
19½Ã 34:19 Many are the afflictions of the righteous, but the LORD rescues them from them all.
19½Ã 34:20 He keeps all their bones; not one of them will be broken.
19½Ã 34:21 Evil brings death to the wicked, and those who hate the righteous will be condemned.
19½Ã 34:22 The LORD redeems the life of his servants; none of those who take refuge in him will be condemned.
19½Ã 35:1 Of David. Contend, O LORD, with those who contend with me; fight against those who fight against me!
19½Ã 35:2 Take hold of shield and buckler, and rise up to help me!
19½Ã 35:3 Draw the spear and javelin against my pursuers; say to my soul, "I am your salvation."
19½Ã 35:4 Let them be put to shame and dishonor who seek after my life. Let them be turned back and confounded who devise evil against me.
19½Ã 35:5 Let them be like chaff before the wind, with the angel of the LORD driving them on.
19½Ã 35:6 Let their way be dark and slippery, with the angel of the LORD pursuing them.
19½Ã 35:7 For without cause they hid their net for me; without cause they dug a pit for my life.
19½Ã 35:8 Let ruin come on them unawares. And let the net that they hid ensnare them; let them fall in it--to their ruin.
19½Ã 35:9 Then my soul shall rejoice in the LORD, exulting in his deliverance.
19½Ã 35:10 All my bones shall say, "O LORD, who is like you? You deliver the weak from those too strong for them, the weak and needy from those who despoil them."
19½Ã 35:11 Malicious witnesses rise up; they ask me about things I do not know.
19½Ã 35:12 They repay me evil for good; my soul is forlorn.
19½Ã 35:13 But as for me, when they were sick, I wore sackcloth; I afflicted myself with fasting. I prayed with head bowed on my bosom,
19½Ã 35:14 as though I grieved for a friend or a brother; I went about as one who laments for a mother, bowed down and in mourning.
19½Ã 35:15 But at my stumbling they gathered in glee, they gathered together against me; ruffians whom I did not know tore at me without ceasing;
19½Ã 35:16 they impiously mocked more and more, gnashing at me with their teeth.
19½Ã 35:17 How long, O LORD, will you look on? Rescue me from their ravages, my life from the lions!
19½Ã 35:18 Then I will thank you in the great congregation; in the mighty throng I will praise you.
19½Ã 35:19 Do not let my treacherous enemies rejoice over me, or those who hate me without cause wink the eye.
19½Ã 35:20 For they do not speak peace, but they conceive deceitful words against those who are quiet in the land.
19½Ã 35:21 They open wide their mouths against me; they say, "Aha, Aha, our eyes have seen it."
19½Ã 35:22 You have seen, O LORD; do not be silent! O Lord, do not be far from me!
19½Ã 35:23 Wake up! Bestir yourself for my defense, for my cause, my God and my Lord!
19½Ã 35:24 Vindicate me, O LORD, my God, according to your righteousness, and do not let them rejoice over me.
19½Ã 35:25 Do not let them say to themselves, "Aha, we have our heart's desire." Do not let them say, "We have swallowed you up."
19½Ã 35:26 Let all those who rejoice at my calamity be put to shame and confusion; let those who exalt themselves against me be clothed with shame and dishonor.
19½Ã 35:27 Let those who desire my vindication shout for joy and be glad, and say evermore, "Great is the LORD, who delights in the welfare of his servant."
19½Ã 35:28 Then my tongue shall tell of your righteousness and of your praise all day long.
19½Ã 36:1 To the leader. Of David, the servant of the LORD. Transgression speaks to the wicked deep in their hearts; there is no fear of God before their eyes.
19½Ã 36:2 For they flatter themselves in their own eyes that their iniquity cannot be found out and hated.
19½Ã 36:3 The words of their mouths are mischief and deceit; they have ceased to act wisely and do good.
19½Ã 36:4 They plot mischief while on their beds; they are set on a way that is not good; they do not reject evil.
19½Ã 36:5 Your steadfast love, O LORD, extends to the heavens, your faithfulness to the clouds.
19½Ã 36:6 Your righteousness is like the mighty mountains, your judgments are like the great deep; you save humans and animals alike, O LORD.
19½Ã 36:7 How precious is your steadfast love, O God! All people may take refuge in the shadow of your wings.
19½Ã 36:8 They feast on the abundance of your house, and you give them drink from the river of your delights.
19½Ã 36:9 For with you is the fountain of life; in your light we see light.
19½Ã 36:10 O continue your steadfast love to those who know you, and your salvation to the upright of heart!
19½Ã 36:11 Do not let the foot of the arrogant tread on me, or the hand of the wicked drive me away.
19½Ã 36:12 There the evildoers lie prostrate; they are thrust down, unable to rise.
19½Ã 37:1 Of David. Do not fret because of the wicked; do not be envious of wrongdoers,
19½Ã 37:2 for they will soon fade like the grass, and wither like the green herb.
19½Ã 37:3 Trust in the LORD, and do good; so you will live in the land, and enjoy security.
19½Ã 37:4 Take delight in the LORD, and he will give you the desires of your heart.
19½Ã 37:5 Commit your way to the LORD; trust in him, and he will act.
19½Ã 37:6 He will make your vindication shine like the light, and the justice of your cause like the noonday.
19½Ã 37:7 Be still before the LORD, and wait patiently for him; do not fret over those who prosper in their way, over those who carry out evil devices.
19½Ã 37:8 Refrain from anger, and forsake wrath. Do not fret--it leads only to evil.
19½Ã 37:9 For the wicked shall be cut off, but those who wait for the LORD shall inherit the land.
19½Ã 37:10 Yet a little while, and the wicked will be no more; though you look diligently for their place, they will not be there.
19½Ã 37:11 But the meek shall inherit the land, and delight themselves in abundant prosperity.
19½Ã 37:12 The wicked plot against the righteous, and gnash their teeth at them;
19½Ã 37:13 but the LORD laughs at the wicked, for he sees that their day is coming.
19½Ã 37:14 The wicked draw the sword and bend their bows to bring down the poor and needy, to kill those who walk uprightly;
19½Ã 37:15 their sword shall enter their own heart, and their bows shall be broken.
19½Ã 37:16 Better is a little that the righteous one has than the abundance of many wicked.
19½Ã 37:17 For the arms of the wicked shall be broken, but the LORD upholds the righteous.
19½Ã 37:18 The LORD knows the days of the blameless, and their heritage will abide forever;
19½Ã 37:19 they are not put to shame in evil times, in the days of famine they have abundance.
19½Ã 37:20 But the wicked perish, and the enemies of the LORD are like the glory of the pastures; they vanish--like smoke they vanish away.
19½Ã 37:21 The wicked borrow, and do not pay back, but the righteous are generous and keep giving;
19½Ã 37:22 for those blessed by the LORD shall inherit the land, but those cursed by him shall be cut off.
19½Ã 37:23 Our steps are made firm by the LORD, when he delights in our way;
19½Ã 37:24 though we stumble, we shall not fall headlong, for the LORD holds us by the hand.
19½Ã 37:25 I have been young, and now am old, yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken or their children begging bread.
19½Ã 37:26 They are ever giving liberally and lending, and their children become a blessing.
19½Ã 37:27 Depart from evil, and do good; so you shall abide forever.
19½Ã 37:28 For the LORD loves justice; he will not forsake his faithful ones. The righteous shall be kept safe forever, but the children of the wicked shall be cut off.
19½Ã 37:29 The righteous shall inherit the land, and live in it forever.
19½Ã 37:30 The mouths of the righteous utter wisdom, and their tongues speak justice.
19½Ã 37:31 The law of their God is in their hearts; their steps do not slip.
19½Ã 37:32 The wicked watch for the righteous, and seek to kill them.
19½Ã 37:33 The LORD will not abandon them to their power, or let them be condemned when they are brought to trial.
19½Ã 37:34 Wait for the LORD, and keep to his way, and he will exalt you to inherit the land; you will look on the destruction of the wicked.
19½Ã 37:35 I have seen the wicked oppressing, and towering like a cedar of Lebanon.
19½Ã 37:36 Again I passed by, and they were no more; though I sought them, they could not be found.
19½Ã 37:37 Mark the blameless, and behold the upright, for there is posterity for the peaceable.
19½Ã 37:38 But transgressors shall be altogether destroyed; the posterity of the wicked shall be cut off.
19½Ã 37:39 The salvation of the righteous is from the LORD; he is their refuge in the time of trouble.
19½Ã 37:40 The LORD helps them and rescues them; he rescues them from the wicked, and saves them, because they take refuge in him.
19½Ã 38:1 A Psalm of David, for the memorial offering. O LORD, do not rebuke me in your anger, or discipline me in your wrath.
19½Ã 38:2 For your arrows have sunk into me, and your hand has come down on me.
19½Ã 38:3 There is no soundness in my flesh because of your indignation; there is no health in my bones because of my sin.
19½Ã 38:4 For my iniquities have gone over my head; they weigh like a burden too heavy for me.
19½Ã 38:5 My wounds grow foul and fester because of my foolishness;
19½Ã 38:6 I am utterly bowed down and prostrate; all day long I go around mourning.
19½Ã 38:7 For my loins are filled with burning, and there is no soundness in my flesh.
19½Ã 38:8 I am utterly spent and crushed; I groan because of the tumult of my heart.
19½Ã 38:9 O Lord, all my longing is known to you; my sighing is not hidden from you.
19½Ã 38:10 My heart throbs, my strength fails me; as for the light of my eyes--it also has gone from me.
19½Ã 38:11 My friends and companions stand aloof from my affliction, and my neighbors stand far off.
19½Ã 38:12 Those who seek my life lay their snares; those who seek to hurt me speak of ruin, and meditate treachery all day long.
19½Ã 38:13 But I am like the deaf, I do not hear; like the mute, who cannot speak.
19½Ã 38:14 Truly, I am like one who does not hear, and in whose mouth is no retort.
19½Ã 38:15 But it is for you, O LORD, that I wait; it is you, O LORD my God, who will answer.
19½Ã 38:16 For I pray, "Only do not let them rejoice over me, those who boast against me when my foot slips."
19½Ã 38:17 For I am ready to fall, and my pain is ever with me.
19½Ã 38:18 I confess my iniquity; I am sorry for my sin.
19½Ã 38:19 Those who are my foes without cause are mighty, and many are those who hate me wrongfully.
19½Ã 38:20 Those who render me evil for good are my adversaries because I follow after good.
19½Ã 38:21 Do not forsake me, O LORD; O my God, do not be far from me;
19½Ã 38:22 make haste to help me, O Lord, my salvation.
19½Ã 39:1 To the leader: to Jeduthun. A Psalm of David. I said, "I will guard my ways that I may not sin with my tongue; I will keep a muzzle on my mouth as long as the wicked are in my presence."
19½Ã 39:2 I was silent and still; I held my peace to no avail; my distress grew worse,
19½Ã 39:3 my heart became hot within me. While I mused, the fire burned; then I spoke with my tongue:
19½Ã 39:4 "LORD, let me know my end, and what is the measure of my days; let me know how fleeting my life is.
19½Ã 39:5 You have made my days a few handbreadths, and my lifetime is as nothing in your sight. Surely everyone stands as a mere breath. Selah
19½Ã 39:6 Surely everyone goes about like a shadow. Surely for nothing they are in turmoil; they heap up, and do not know who will gather.
19½Ã 39:7 "And now, O Lord, what do I wait for? My hope is in you.
19½Ã 39:8 Deliver me from all my transgressions. Do not make me the scorn of the fool.
19½Ã 39:9 I am silent; I do not open my mouth, for it is you who have done it.
19½Ã 39:10 Remove your stroke from me; I am worn down by the blows of your hand.
19½Ã 39:11 "You chastise mortals in punishment for sin, consuming like a moth what is dear to them; surely everyone is a mere breath. Selah
19½Ã 39:12 "Hear my prayer, O LORD, and give ear to my cry; do not hold your peace at my tears. For I am your passing guest, an alien, like all my forebears.
19½Ã 39:13 Turn your gaze away from me, that I may smile again, before I depart and am no more."
19½Ã 40:1 To the leader. Of David. A Psalm. I waited patiently for the LORD; he inclined to me and heard my cry.
19½Ã 40:2 He drew me up from the desolate pit, out of the miry bog, and set my feet upon a rock, making my steps secure.
19½Ã 40:3 He put a new song in my mouth, a song of praise to our God. Many will see and fear, and put their trust in the LORD.
19½Ã 40:4 Happy are those who make the LORD their trust, who do not turn to the proud, to those who go astray after false gods.
19½Ã 40:5 You have multiplied, O LORD my God, your wondrous deeds and your thoughts toward us; none can compare with you. Were I to proclaim and tell of them, they would be more than can be counted.
19½Ã 40:6 Sacrifice and offering you do not desire, but you have given me an open ear. Burnt offering and sin offering you have not required.
19½Ã 40:7 Then I said, "Here I am; in the scroll of the book it is written of me.
19½Ã 40:8 I delight to do your will, O my God; your law is within my heart."
19½Ã 40:9 I have told the glad news of deliverance in the great congregation; see, I have not restrained my lips, as you know, O LORD.
19½Ã 40:10 I have not hidden your saving help within my heart, I have spoken of your faithfulness and your salvation; I have not concealed your steadfast love and your faithfulness from the great congregation.
19½Ã 40:11 Do not, O LORD, withhold your mercy from me; let your steadfast love and your faithfulness keep me safe forever.
19½Ã 40:12 For evils have encompassed me without number; my iniquities have overtaken me, until I cannot see; they are more than the hairs of my head, and my heart fails me.
19½Ã 40:13 Be pleased, O LORD, to deliver me; O LORD, make haste to help me.
19½Ã 40:14 Let all those be put to shame and confusion who seek to snatch away my life; let those be turned back and brought to dishonor who desire my hurt.
19½Ã 40:15 Let those be appalled because of their shame who say to me, "Aha, Aha!"
19½Ã 40:16 But may all who seek you rejoice and be glad in you; may those who love your salvation say continually, "Great is the LORD!"
19½Ã 40:17 As for me, I am poor and needy, but the Lord takes thought for me. You are my help and my deliverer; do not delay, O my God.
19½Ã 41:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. Happy are those who consider the poor; the LORD delivers them in the day of trouble.
19½Ã 41:2 The LORD protects them and keeps them alive; they are called happy in the land. You do not give them up to the will of their enemies.
19½Ã 41:3 The LORD sustains them on their sickbed; in their illness you heal all their infirmities.
19½Ã 41:4 As for me, I said, "O LORD, be gracious to me; heal me, for I have sinned against you."
19½Ã 41:5 My enemies wonder in malice when I will die, and my name perish.
19½Ã 41:6 And when they come to see me, they utter empty words, while their hearts gather mischief; when they go out, they tell it abroad.
19½Ã 41:7 All who hate me whisper together about me; they imagine the worst for me.
