19½Ã 62:1 To the leader: according to Jeduthun. A Psalm of David. For God alone my soul waits in silence; from him comes my salvation.
19½Ã 62:2 He alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress; I shall never be shaken.
19½Ã 62:3 How long will you assail a person, will you batter your victim, all of you, as you would a leaning wall, a tottering fence?
19½Ã 62:4 Their only plan is to bring down a person of prominence. They take pleasure in falsehood; they bless with their mouths, but inwardly they curse. Selah
19½Ã 62:5 For God alone my soul waits in silence, for my hope is from him.
19½Ã 62:6 He alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress; I shall not be shaken.
