19½Ã 63:1 A Psalm of David, when he was in the Wilderness of Judah. O God, you are my God, I seek you, my soul thirsts for you; my flesh faints for you, as in a dry and weary land where there is no water.
19½Ã 63:2 So I have looked upon you in the sanctuary, beholding your power and glory.
19½Ã 63:3 Because your steadfast love is better than life, my lips will praise you.
19½Ã 63:4 So I will bless you as long as I live; I will lift up my hands and call on your name.
19½Ã 63:5 My soul is satisfied as with a rich feast, and my mouth praises you with joyful lips
