19½Ã 82:1 A Psalm of Asaph. God has taken his place in the divine council; in the midst of the gods he holds judgment:
19½Ã 82:2 "How long will you judge unjustly and show partiality to the wicked? Selah
19½Ã 82:3 Give justice to the weak and the orphan; maintain the right of the lowly and the destitute.
19½Ã 82:4 Rescue the weak and the needy; deliver them from the hand of the wicked."
19½Ã 82:5 They have neither knowledge nor understanding, they walk around in darkness; all the foundations of the earth are shaken.
19½Ã 82:6 I say, "You are gods, children of the Most High, all of you;
