19½Ã 83:1 A Song. A Psalm of Asaph. O God, do not keep silence; do not hold your peace or be still, O God!
19½Ã 83:2 Even now your enemies are in tumult; those who hate you have raised their heads.
19½Ã 83:3 They lay crafty plans against your people; they consult together against those you protect.
19½Ã 83:4 They say, "Come, let us wipe them out as a nation; let the name of Israel be remembered no more."
19½Ã 83:5 They conspire with one accord; against you they make a covenant--
