19½Ã 84:1 To the leader: according to The Gittith. Of the Korahites. A Psalm. How lovely is your dwelling place, O LORD of hosts!
19½Ã 84:2 My soul longs, indeed it faints for the courts of the LORD; my heart and my flesh sing for joy to the living God.
19½Ã 84:3 Even the sparrow finds a home, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young, at your altars, O LORD of hosts, my King and my God.
19½Ã 84:4 Happy are those who live in your house, ever singing your praise. Selah
19½Ã 84:5 Happy are those whose strength is in you, in whose heart are the highways to Zion.
