19½Ã 86:1 A Prayer of David. Incline your ear, O LORD, and answer me, for I am poor and needy.
19½Ã 86:2 Preserve my life, for I am devoted to you; save your servant who trusts in you. You are my God;
19½Ã 86:3 be gracious to me, O Lord, for to you do I cry all day long.
19½Ã 86:4 Gladden the soul of your servant, for to you, O Lord, I lift up my soul.
19½Ã 86:5 For you, O Lord, are good and forgiving, abounding in steadfast love to all who call on you.
19½Ã 86:6 Give ear, O LORD, to my prayer; listen to my cry of supplication.
19½Ã 86:7 In the day of my trouble I call on you, for you will answer me.
19½Ã 86:8 There is none like you among the gods, O Lord, nor are there any works like yours.
19½Ã 86:9 All the nations you have made shall come and bow down before you, O Lord, and shall glorify your name.
19½Ã 86:10 For you are great and do wondrous things; you alone are God.
19½Ã 86:11 Teach me your way, O LORD, that I may walk in your truth; give me an undivided heart to revere your name.
19½Ã 86:12 I give thanks to you, O Lord my God, with my whole heart, and I will glorify your name forever.
19½Ã 86:13 For great is your steadfast love toward me; you have delivered my soul from the depths of Sheol.
19½Ã 86:14 O God, the insolent rise up against me; a band of ruffians seeks my life, and they do not set you before them.
19½Ã 86:15 But you, O Lord, are a God merciful and gracious, slow to anger and abounding in steadfast love and faithfulness.
19½Ã 86:16 Turn to me and be gracious to me; give your strength to your servant; save the child of your serving girl.
19½Ã 86:17 Show me a sign of your favor, so that those who hate me may see it and be put to shame, because you, LORD, have helped me and comforted me.
19½Ã 87:1 Of the Korahites. A Psalm. A Song. On the holy mount stands the city he founded;
