19½Ã 89:29 I will establish his line forever, and his throne as long as the heavens endure.
19½Ã 89:30 If his children forsake my law and do not walk according to my ordinances,
19½Ã 89:31 if they violate my statutes and do not keep my commandments,
19½Ã 89:32 then I will punish their transgression with the rod and their iniquity with scourges;
19½Ã 89:33 but I will not remove from him my steadfast love, or be false to my faithfulness.
19½Ã 89:34 I will not violate my covenant, or alter the word that went forth from my lips.
19½Ã 89:35 Once and for all I have sworn by my holiness; I will not lie to David.
19½Ã 89:36 His line shall continue forever, and his throne endure before me like the sun.
19½Ã 89:37 It shall be established forever like the moon, an enduring witness in the skies." Selah
19½Ã 89:38 But now you have spurned and rejected him; you are full of wrath against your anointed.
19½Ã 89:39 You have renounced the covenant with your servant; you have defiled his crown in the dust.
19½Ã 89:40 You have broken through all his walls; you have laid his strongholds in ruins.
19½Ã 89:41 All who pass by plunder him; he has become the scorn of his neighbors.
19½Ã 89:42 You have exalted the right hand of his foes; you have made all his enemies rejoice.
19½Ã 89:43 Moreover, you have turned back the edge of his sword, and you have not supported him in battle.
19½Ã 89:44 You have removed the scepter from his hand, and hurled his throne to the ground.
19½Ã 89:45 You have cut short the days of his youth; you have covered him with shame. Selah
19½Ã 89:46 How long, O LORD? Will you hide yourself forever? How long will your wrath burn like fire?
