19½Ã 89:48 Who can live and never see death? Who can escape the power of Sheol? Selah
19½Ã 89:49 Lord, where is your steadfast love of old, which by your faithfulness you swore to David?
19½Ã 89:50 Remember, O Lord, how your servant is taunted; how I bear in my bosom the insults of the peoples,
19½Ã 89:51 with which your enemies taunt, O LORD, with which they taunted the footsteps of your anointed.
19½Ã 89:52 Blessed be the LORD forever. Amen and Amen.
19½Ã 90:1 A Prayer of Moses, the man of God. Lord, you have been our dwelling place in all generations.
19½Ã 90:2 Before the mountains were brought forth, or ever you had formed the earth and the world, from everlasting to everlasting you are God.
19½Ã 90:3 You turn us back to dust, and say, "Turn back, you mortals."
19½Ã 90:4 For a thousand years in your sight are like yesterday when it is past, or like a watch in the night.
19½Ã 90:5 You sweep them away; they are like a dream, like grass that is renewed in the morning;
19½Ã 90:6 in the morning it flourishes and is renewed; in the evening it fades and withers.
19½Ã 90:7 For we are consumed by your anger; by your wrath we are overwhelmed.
19½Ã 90:8 You have set our iniquities before you, our secret sins in the light of your countenance.
19½Ã 90:9 For all our days pass away under your wrath; our years come to an end like a sigh.
19½Ã 90:10 The days of our life are seventy years, or perhaps eighty, if we are strong; even then their span is only toil and trouble; they are soon gone, and we fly away.
19½Ã 90:11 Who considers the power of your anger? Your wrath is as great as the fear that is due you.
19½Ã 90:12 So teach us to count our days that we may gain a wise heart.
19½Ã 90:13 Turn, O LORD! How long? Have compassion on your servants!
19½Ã 90:14 Satisfy us in the morning with your steadfast love, so that we may rejoice and be glad all our days.
19½Ã 90:15 Make us glad as many days as you have afflicted us, and as many years as we have seen evil.
19½Ã 90:16 Let your work be manifest to your servants, and your glorious power to their children.
19½Ã 90:17 Let the favor of the Lord our God be upon us, and prosper for us the work of our hands--O prosper the work of our hands!
19½Ã 91:1 You who live in the shelter of the Most High, who abide in the shadow of the Almighty,
