19½Ã 92:7 though the wicked sprout like grass and all evildoers flourish, they are doomed to destruction forever,
19½Ã 92:8 but you, O LORD, are on high forever.
19½Ã 92:9 For your enemies, O LORD, for your enemies shall perish; all evildoers shall be scattered.
19½Ã 92:10 But you have exalted my horn like that of the wild ox; you have poured over me fresh oil.
19½Ã 92:11 My eyes have seen the downfall of my enemies; my ears have heard the doom of my evil assailants.
19½Ã 92:12 The righteous flourish like the palm tree, and grow like a cedar in Lebanon.
19½Ã 92:13 They are planted in the house of the LORD; they flourish in the courts of our God.
19½Ã 92:14 In old age they still produce fruit; they are always green and full of sap,
19½Ã 92:15 showing that the LORD is upright; he is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.
