19½Ã 94:1 O LORD, you God of vengeance, you God of vengeance, shine forth!
19½Ã 94:2 Rise up, O judge of the earth; give to the proud what they deserve!
19½Ã 94:3 O LORD, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked exult?
19½Ã 94:4 They pour out their arrogant words; all the evildoers boast.
19½Ã 94:5 They crush your people, O LORD, and afflict your heritage.
19½Ã 94:6 They kill the widow and the stranger, they murder the orphan,
19½Ã 94:7 and they say, "The LORD does not see; the God of Jacob does not perceive."
19½Ã 94:8 Understand, O dullest of the people; fools, when will you be wise?
19½Ã 94:9 He who planted the ear, does he not hear? He who formed the eye, does he not see?
19½Ã 94:10 He who disciplines the nations, he who teaches knowledge to humankind, does he not chastise?
19½Ã 94:11 The LORD knows our thoughts, that they are but an empty breath.
19½Ã 94:12 Happy are those whom you discipline, O LORD, and whom you teach out of your law,
19½Ã 94:13 giving them respite from days of trouble, until a pit is dug for the wicked.
19½Ã 94:14 For the LORD will not forsake his people; he will not abandon his heritage;
