19½Ã 94:16 Who rises up for me against the wicked? Who stands up for me against evildoers?
19½Ã 94:17 If the LORD had not been my help, my soul would soon have lived in the land of silence.
19½Ã 94:18 When I thought, "My foot is slipping," your steadfast love, O LORD, held me up.
19½Ã 94:19 When the cares of my heart are many, your consolations cheer my soul.
19½Ã 94:20 Can wicked rulers be allied with you, those who contrive mischief by statute?
19½Ã 94:21 They band together against the life of the righteous, and condemn the innocent to death.
19½Ã 94:22 But the LORD has become my stronghold, and my God the rock of my refuge.
19½Ã 94:23 He will repay them for their iniquity and wipe them out for their wickedness; the LORD our God will wipe them out.
