19½Ã 100:1 A Psalm of thanksgiving. Make a joyful noise to the LORD, all the earth.
19½Ã 100:2 Worship the LORD with gladness; come into his presence with singing.
19½Ã 100:3 Know that the LORD is God. It is he that made us, and we are his; we are his people, and the sheep of his pasture.
19½Ã 100:4 Enter his gates with thanksgiving, and his courts with praise. Give thanks to him, bless his name.
19½Ã 100:5 For the LORD is good; his steadfast love endures forever, and his faithfulness to all generations.
19½Ã 101:1 Of David. A Psalm. I will sing of loyalty and of justice; to you, O LORD, I will sing.
19½Ã 101:2 I will study the way that is blameless. When shall I attain it? I will walk with integrity of heart within my house;
19½Ã 101:3 I will not set before my eyes anything that is base. I hate the work of those who fall away; it shall not cling to me.
19½Ã 101:4 Perverseness of heart shall be far from me; I will know nothing of evil.
19½Ã 101:5 One who secretly slanders a neighbor I will destroy. A haughty look and an arrogant heart I will not tolerate.
19½Ã 101:6 I will look with favor on the faithful in the land, so that they may live with me; whoever walks in the way that is blameless shall minister to me.
19½Ã 101:7 No one who practices deceit shall remain in my house; no one who utters lies shall continue in my presence.
19½Ã 101:8 Morning by morning I will destroy all the wicked in the land, cutting off all evildoers from the city of the LORD.
19½Ã 102:1 A prayer of one afflicted, when faint and pleading before the LORD. Hear my prayer, O LORD; let my cry come to you.
19½Ã 102:2 Do not hide your face from me in the day of my distress. Incline your ear to me; answer me speedily in the day when I call.
19½Ã 102:3 For my days pass away like smoke, and my bones burn like a furnace.
19½Ã 102:4 My heart is stricken and withered like grass; I am too wasted to eat my bread.
19½Ã 102:5 Because of my loud groaning my bones cling to my skin.
19½Ã 102:6 I am like an owl of the wilderness, like a little owl of the waste places.
19½Ã 102:7 I lie awake; I am like a lonely bird on the housetop.
19½Ã 102:8 All day long my enemies taunt me; those who deride me use my name for a curse.
19½Ã 102:9 For I eat ashes like bread, and mingle tears with my drink,
19½Ã 102:10 because of your indignation and anger; for you have lifted me up and thrown me aside.
19½Ã 102:11 My days are like an evening shadow; I wither away like grass.
19½Ã 102:12 But you, O LORD, are enthroned forever; your name endures to all generations.
19½Ã 102:13 You will rise up and have compassion on Zion, for it is time to favor it; the appointed time has come.
19½Ã 102:14 For your servants hold its stones dear, and have pity on its dust.
19½Ã 102:15 The nations will fear the name of the LORD, and all the kings of the earth your glory.
19½Ã 102:16 For the LORD will build up Zion; he will appear in his glory.
19½Ã 102:17 He will regard the prayer of the destitute, and will not despise their prayer.
19½Ã 102:18 Let this be recorded for a generation to come, so that a people yet unborn may praise the LORD:
19½Ã 102:19 that he looked down from his holy height, from heaven the LORD looked at the earth,
19½Ã 102:20 to hear the groans of the prisoners, to set free those who were doomed to die;
19½Ã 102:21 so that the name of the LORD may be declared in Zion, and his praise in Jerusalem,
19½Ã 102:22 when peoples gather together, and kingdoms, to worship the LORD.
19½Ã 102:23 He has broken my strength in midcourse; he has shortened my days.
19½Ã 102:24 "O my God," I say, "do not take me away at the mid-point of my life, you whose years endure throughout all generations."
19½Ã 102:25 Long ago you laid the foundation of the earth, and the heavens are the work of your hands.
19½Ã 102:26 They will perish, but you endure; they will all wear out like a garment. You change them like clothing, and they pass away;
19½Ã 102:27 but you are the same, and your years have no end.
19½Ã 102:28 The children of your servants shall live secure; their offspring shall be established in your presence.
19½Ã 103:1 Of David. Bless the LORD, O my soul, and all that is within me, bless his holy name.
19½Ã 103:2 Bless the LORD, O my soul, and do not forget all his benefits--
19½Ã 103:3 who forgives all your iniquity, who heals all your diseases,
19½Ã 103:4 who redeems your life from the Pit, who crowns you with steadfast love and mercy,
19½Ã 103:5 who satisfies you with good as long as you live so that your youth is renewed like the eagle's.
19½Ã 103:6 The LORD works vindication and justice for all who are oppressed.
19½Ã 103:7 He made known his ways to Moses, his acts to the people of Israel.
19½Ã 103:8 The LORD is merciful and gracious, slow to anger and abounding in steadfast love.
19½Ã 103:9 He will not always accuse, nor will he keep his anger forever.
19½Ã 103:10 He does not deal with us according to our sins, nor repay us according to our iniquities.
19½Ã 103:11 For as the heavens are high above the earth, so great is his steadfast love toward those who fear him;
19½Ã 103:12 as far as the east is from the west, so far he removes our transgressions from us.
19½Ã 103:13 As a father has compassion for his children, so the LORD has compassion for those who fear him.
19½Ã 103:14 For he knows how we were made; he remembers that we are dust.
