19½Ã 105:6 O offspring of his servant Abraham, children of Jacob, his chosen ones.
19½Ã 105:7 He is the LORD our God; his judgments are in all the earth.
19½Ã 105:8 He is mindful of his covenant forever, of the word that he commanded, for a thousand generations,
19½Ã 105:9 the covenant that he made with Abraham, his sworn promise to Isaac,
19½Ã 105:10 which he confirmed to Jacob as a statute, to Israel as an everlasting covenant,
19½Ã 105:11 saying, "To you I will give the land of Canaan as your portion for an inheritance."
19½Ã 105:12 When they were few in number, of little account, and strangers in it,
19½Ã 105:13 wandering from nation to nation, from one kingdom to another people,
19½Ã 105:14 he allowed no one to oppress them; he rebuked kings on their account,
19½Ã 105:15 saying, "Do not touch my anointed ones; do my prophets no harm."
19½Ã 105:16 When he summoned famine against the land, and broke every staff of bread,
19½Ã 105:17 he had sent a man ahead of them, Joseph, who was sold as a slave.
19½Ã 105:18 His feet were hurt with fetters, his neck was put in a collar of iron;
19½Ã 105:19 until what he had said came to pass, the word of the LORD kept testing him.
19½Ã 105:20 The king sent and released him; the ruler of the peoples set him free.
19½Ã 105:21 He made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his possessions,
19½Ã 105:22 to instruct his officials at his pleasure, and to teach his elders wisdom.
19½Ã 105:23 Then Israel came to Egypt; Jacob lived as an alien in the land of Ham.
19½Ã 105:24 And the LORD made his people very fruitful, and made them stronger than their foes,
19½Ã 105:25 whose hearts he then turned to hate his people, to deal craftily with his servants.
19½Ã 105:26 He sent his servant Moses, and Aaron whom he had chosen.
19½Ã 105:27 They performed his signs among them, and miracles in the land of Ham.
19½Ã 105:28 He sent darkness, and made the land dark; they rebelled against his words.
19½Ã 105:29 He turned their waters into blood, and caused their fish to die.
19½Ã 105:30 Their land swarmed with frogs, even in the chambers of their kings.
19½Ã 105:31 He spoke, and there came swarms of flies, and gnats throughout their country.
19½Ã 105:32 He gave them hail for rain, and lightning that flashed through their land.
19½Ã 105:33 He struck their vines and fig trees, and shattered the trees of their country.
19½Ã 105:34 He spoke, and the locusts came, and young locusts without number;
19½Ã 105:35 they devoured all the vegetation in their land, and ate up the fruit of their ground.
19½Ã 105:36 He struck down all the firstborn in their land, the first issue of all their strength.
19½Ã 105:37 Then he brought Israel out with silver and gold, and there was no one among their tribes who stumbled.
19½Ã 105:38 Egypt was glad when they departed, for dread of them had fallen upon it.
19½Ã 105:39 He spread a cloud for a covering, and fire to give light by night.
19½Ã 105:40 They asked, and he brought quails, and gave them food from heaven in abundance.
19½Ã 105:41 He opened the rock, and water gushed out; it flowed through the desert like a river.
19½Ã 105:42 For he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham, his servant.
19½Ã 105:43 So he brought his people out with joy, his chosen ones with singing.
19½Ã 105:44 He gave them the lands of the nations, and they took possession of the wealth of the peoples,
19½Ã 105:45 that they might keep his statutes and observe his laws. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 106:1 Praise the LORD! O give thanks to the LORD, for he is good; for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 106:2 Who can utter the mighty doings of the LORD, or declare all his praise?
19½Ã 106:3 Happy are those who observe justice, who do righteousness at all times.
19½Ã 106:4 Remember me, O LORD, when you show favor to your people; help me when you deliver them;
19½Ã 106:5 that I may see the prosperity of your chosen ones, that I may rejoice in the gladness of your nation, that I may glory in your heritage.
19½Ã 106:6 Both we and our ancestors have sinned; we have committed iniquity, have done wickedly.
19½Ã 106:7 Our ancestors, when they were in Egypt, did not consider your wonderful works; they did not remember the abundance of your steadfast love, but rebelled against the Most High at the Red Sea.
19½Ã 106:8 Yet he saved them for his name's sake, so that he might make known his mighty power.
19½Ã 106:9 He rebuked the Red Sea, and it became dry; he led them through the deep as through a desert.
19½Ã 106:10 So he saved them from the hand of the foe, and delivered them from the hand of the enemy.
19½Ã 106:11 The waters covered their adversaries; not one of them was left.
19½Ã 106:12 Then they believed his words; they sang his praise.
19½Ã 106:13 But they soon forgot his works; they did not wait for his counsel.
19½Ã 106:14 But they had a wanton craving in the wilderness, and put God to the test in the desert;
19½Ã 106:15 he gave them what they asked, but sent a wasting disease among them.
19½Ã 106:16 They were jealous of Moses in the camp, and of Aaron, the holy one of the LORD.
19½Ã 106:17 The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the faction of Abiram.
19½Ã 106:18 Fire also broke out in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.
19½Ã 106:19 They made a calf at Horeb and worshiped a cast image.
19½Ã 106:20 They exchanged the glory of God for the image of an ox that eats grass.
19½Ã 106:21 They forgot God, their Savior, who had done great things in Egypt,
19½Ã 106:22 wondrous works in the land of Ham, and awesome deeds by the Red Sea.
19½Ã 106:23 Therefore he said he would destroy them--had not Moses, his chosen one, stood in the breach before him, to turn away his wrath from destroying them.
19½Ã 106:24 Then they despised the pleasant land, having no faith in his promise.
19½Ã 106:25 They grumbled in their tents, and did not obey the voice of the LORD.
19½Ã 106:26 Therefore he raised his hand and swore to them that he would make them fall in the wilderness,
19½Ã 106:27 and would disperse their descendants among the nations, scattering them over the lands.
19½Ã 106:28 Then they attached themselves to the Baal of Peor, and ate sacrifices offered to the dead;
19½Ã 106:29 they provoked the LORD to anger with their deeds, and a plague broke out among them.
19½Ã 106:30 Then Phinehas stood up and interceded, and the plague was stopped.
19½Ã 106:31 And that has been reckoned to him as righteousness from generation to generation forever.
19½Ã 106:32 They angered the LORD at the waters of Meribah, and it went ill with Moses on their account;
19½Ã 106:33 for they made his spirit bitter, and he spoke words that were rash.
19½Ã 106:34 They did not destroy the peoples, as the LORD commanded them,
19½Ã 106:35 but they mingled with the nations and learned to do as they did.
19½Ã 106:36 They served their idols, which became a snare to them.
19½Ã 106:37 They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to the demons;
19½Ã 106:38 they poured out innocent blood, the blood of their sons and daughters, whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan; and the land was polluted with blood.
19½Ã 106:39 Thus they became unclean by their acts, and prostituted themselves in their doings.
19½Ã 106:40 Then the anger of the LORD was kindled against his people, and he abhorred his heritage;
19½Ã 106:41 he gave them into the hand of the nations, so that those who hated them ruled over them.
19½Ã 106:42 Their enemies oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their power.
19½Ã 106:43 Many times he delivered them, but they were rebellious in their purposes, and were brought low through their iniquity.
19½Ã 106:44 Nevertheless he regarded their distress when he heard their cry.
19½Ã 106:45 For their sake he remembered his covenant, and showed compassion according to the abundance of his steadfast love.
19½Ã 106:46 He caused them to be pitied by all who held them captive.
19½Ã 106:47 Save us, O LORD our God, and gather us from among the nations, that we may give thanks to your holy name and glory in your praise.
19½Ã 106:48 Blessed be the LORD, the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting. And let all the people say, "Amen." Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 107:1 O give thanks to the LORD, for he is good; for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 107:2 Let the redeemed of the LORD say so, those he redeemed from trouble
19½Ã 107:3 and gathered in from the lands, from the east and from the west, from the north and from the south.
19½Ã 107:4 Some wandered in desert wastes, finding no way to an inhabited town;
19½Ã 107:5 hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted within them.
19½Ã 107:6 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, and he delivered them from their distress;
19½Ã 107:7 he led them by a straight way, until they reached an inhabited town.
19½Ã 107:8 Let them thank the LORD for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to humankind.
19½Ã 107:9 For he satisfies the thirsty, and the hungry he fills with good things.
19½Ã 107:10 Some sat in darkness and in gloom, prisoners in misery and in irons,
19½Ã 107:11 for they had rebelled against the words of God, and spurned the counsel of the Most High.
19½Ã 107:12 Their hearts were bowed down with hard labor; they fell down, with no one to help.
19½Ã 107:13 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, and he saved them from their distress;
19½Ã 107:14 he brought them out of darkness and gloom, and broke their bonds asunder.
19½Ã 107:15 Let them thank the LORD for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to humankind.
19½Ã 107:16 For he shatters the doors of bronze, and cuts in two the bars of iron.
19½Ã 107:17 Some were sick through their sinful ways, and because of their iniquities endured affliction;
19½Ã 107:18 they loathed any kind of food, and they drew near to the gates of death.
19½Ã 107:19 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, and he saved them from their distress;
19½Ã 107:20 he sent out his word and healed them, and delivered them from destruction.
19½Ã 107:21 Let them thank the LORD for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to humankind.
19½Ã 107:22 And let them offer thanksgiving sacrifices, and tell of his deeds with songs of joy.
19½Ã 107:23 Some went down to the sea in ships, doing business on the mighty waters;
19½Ã 107:24 they saw the deeds of the LORD, his wondrous works in the deep.
19½Ã 107:25 For he commanded and raised the stormy wind, which lifted up the waves of the sea.
19½Ã 107:26 They mounted up to heaven, they went down to the depths; their courage melted away in their calamity;
19½Ã 107:27 they reeled and staggered like drunkards, and were at their wits' end.
19½Ã 107:28 Then they cried to the LORD in their trouble, and he brought them out from their distress;
19½Ã 107:29 he made the storm be still, and the waves of the sea were hushed.
19½Ã 107:30 Then they were glad because they had quiet, and he brought them to their desired haven.
19½Ã 107:31 Let them thank the LORD for his steadfast love, for his wonderful works to humankind.
19½Ã 107:32 Let them extol him in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.
19½Ã 107:33 He turns rivers into a desert, springs of water into thirsty ground,
19½Ã 107:34 a fruitful land into a salty waste, because of the wickedness of its inhabitants.
19½Ã 107:35 He turns a desert into pools of water, a parched land into springs of water.
19½Ã 107:36 And there he lets the hungry live, and they establish a town to live in;
19½Ã 107:37 they sow fields, and plant vineyards, and get a fruitful yield.
19½Ã 107:38 By his blessing they multiply greatly, and he does not let their cattle decrease.
19½Ã 107:39 When they are diminished and brought low through oppression, trouble, and sorrow,
19½Ã 107:40 he pours contempt on princes and makes them wander in trackless wastes;
19½Ã 107:41 but he raises up the needy out of distress, and makes their families like flocks.
19½Ã 107:42 The upright see it and are glad; and all wickedness stops its mouth.
19½Ã 107:43 Let those who are wise give heed to these things, and consider the steadfast love of the LORD.
19½Ã 108:1 A Song. A Psalm of David. My heart is steadfast, O God, my heart is steadfast; I will sing and make melody. Awake, my soul!
19½Ã 108:2 Awake, O harp and lyre! I will awake the dawn.
19½Ã 108:3 I will give thanks to you, O LORD, among the peoples, and I will sing praises to you among the nations.
19½Ã 108:4 For your steadfast love is higher than the heavens, and your faithfulness reaches to the clouds.
19½Ã 108:5 Be exalted, O God, above the heavens. and let your glory be over all the earth.
19½Ã 108:6 Give victory with your right hand, and answer me, so that those whom you love may be rescued.
19½Ã 108:7 God has promised in his sanctuary: "With exultation I will divide up Shechem, and portion out the Vale of Succoth.
19½Ã 108:8 Gilead is mine; Manasseh is mine; Ephraim is my helmet; Judah is my scepter.
19½Ã 108:9 Moab is my washbasin; on Edom I hurl my shoe; over Philistia I shout in triumph."
19½Ã 108:10 Who will bring me to the fortified city? Who will lead me to Edom?
19½Ã 108:11 Have you not rejected us, O God? You do not go out, O God, with our armies.
19½Ã 108:12 O grant us help against the foe, for human help is worthless.
19½Ã 108:13 With God we shall do valiantly; it is he who will tread down our foes.
19½Ã 109:1 To the leader. Of David. A Psalm. Do not be silent, O God of my praise.
19½Ã 109:2 For wicked and deceitful mouths are opened against me, speaking against me with lying tongues.
19½Ã 109:3 They beset me with words of hate, and attack me without cause.
19½Ã 109:4 In return for my love they accuse me, even while I make prayer for them.
19½Ã 109:5 So they reward me evil for good, and hatred for my love.
19½Ã 109:6 They say, "Appoint a wicked man against him; let an accuser stand on his right.
19½Ã 109:7 When he is tried, let him be found guilty; let his prayer be counted as sin.
19½Ã 109:8 May his days be few; may another seize his position.
19½Ã 109:9 May his children be orphans, and his wife a widow.
19½Ã 109:10 May his children wander about and beg; may they be driven out of the ruins they inhabit.
19½Ã 109:11 May the creditor seize all that he has; may strangers plunder the fruits of his toil.
19½Ã 109:12 May there be no one to do him a kindness, nor anyone to pity his orphaned children.
19½Ã 109:13 May his posterity be cut off; may his name be blotted out in the second generation.
19½Ã 109:14 May the iniquity of his father be remembered before the LORD, and do not let the sin of his mother be blotted out.
19½Ã 109:15 Let them be before the LORD continually, and may his memory be cut off from the earth.
19½Ã 109:16 For he did not remember to show kindness, but pursued the poor and needy and the brokenhearted to their death.
19½Ã 109:17 He loved to curse; let curses come on him. He did not like blessing; may it be far from him.
19½Ã 109:18 He clothed himself with cursing as his coat, may it soak into his body like water, like oil into his bones.
19½Ã 109:19 May it be like a garment that he wraps around himself, like a belt that he wears every day."
19½Ã 109:20 May that be the reward of my accusers from the LORD, of those who speak evil against my life.
19½Ã 109:21 But you, O LORD my Lord, act on my behalf for your name's sake; because your steadfast love is good, deliver me.
19½Ã 109:22 For I am poor and needy, and my heart is pierced within me.
19½Ã 109:23 I am gone like a shadow at evening; I am shaken off like a locust.
19½Ã 109:24 My knees are weak through fasting; my body has become gaunt.
19½Ã 109:25 I am an object of scorn to my accusers; when they see me, they shake their heads.
19½Ã 109:26 Help me, O LORD my God! Save me according to your steadfast love.
19½Ã 109:27 Let them know that this is your hand; you, O LORD, have done it.
19½Ã 109:28 Let them curse, but you will bless. Let my assailants be put to shame; may your servant be glad.
19½Ã 109:29 May my accusers be clothed with dishonor; may they be wrapped in their own shame as in a mantle.
19½Ã 109:30 With my mouth I will give great thanks to the LORD; I will praise him in the midst of the throng.
19½Ã 109:31 For he stands at the right hand of the needy, to save them from those who would condemn them to death.
19½Ã 110:1 Of David. A Psalm. The LORD says to my lord, "Sit at my right hand until I make your enemies your footstool."
19½Ã 110:2 The LORD sends out from Zion your mighty scepter. Rule in the midst of your foes.
19½Ã 110:3 Your people will offer themselves willingly on the day you lead your forces on the holy mountains. From the womb of the morning, like dew, your youth will come to you.
19½Ã 110:4 The LORD has sworn and will not change his mind, "You are a priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek."
19½Ã 110:5 The Lord is at your right hand; he will shatter kings on the day of his wrath.
19½Ã 110:6 He will execute judgment among the nations, filling them with corpses; he will shatter heads over the wide earth.
19½Ã 110:7 He will drink from the stream by the path; therefore he will lift up his head.
19½Ã 111:1 Praise the LORD! I will give thanks to the LORD with my whole heart, in the company of the upright, in the congregation.
19½Ã 111:2 Great are the works of the LORD, studied by all who delight in them.
19½Ã 111:3 Full of honor and majesty is his work, and his righteousness endures forever.
19½Ã 111:4 He has gained renown by his wonderful deeds; the LORD is gracious and merciful.
19½Ã 111:5 He provides food for those who fear him; he is ever mindful of his covenant.
19½Ã 111:6 He has shown his people the power of his works, in giving them the heritage of the nations.
19½Ã 111:7 The works of his hands are faithful and just; all his precepts are trustworthy.
19½Ã 111:8 They are established forever and ever, to be performed with faithfulness and uprightness.
19½Ã 111:9 He sent redemption to his people; he has commanded his covenant forever. Holy and awesome is his name.
19½Ã 111:10 The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom; all those who practice it have a good understanding. His praise endures forever.
19½Ã 112:1 Praise the LORD! Happy are those who fear the LORD, who greatly delight in his commandments.
19½Ã 112:2 Their descendants will be mighty in the land; the generation of the upright will be blessed.
19½Ã 112:3 Wealth and riches are in their houses, and their righteousness endures forever.
19½Ã 112:4 They rise in the darkness as a light for the upright; they are gracious, merciful, and righteous.
19½Ã 112:5 It is well with those who deal generously and lend, who conduct their affairs with justice.
19½Ã 112:6 For the righteous will never be moved; they will be remembered forever.
19½Ã 112:7 They are not afraid of evil tidings; their hearts are firm, secure in the LORD.
19½Ã 112:8 Their hearts are steady, they will not be afraid; in the end they will look in triumph on their foes.
19½Ã 112:9 They have distributed freely, they have given to the poor; their righteousness endures forever; their horn is exalted in honor.
19½Ã 112:10 The wicked see it and are angry; they gnash their teeth and melt away; the desire of the wicked comes to nothing.
19½Ã 113:1 Praise the LORD! Praise, O servants of the LORD; praise the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 113:2 Blessed be the name of the LORD from this time on and forevermore.
19½Ã 113:3 From the rising of the sun to its setting the name of the LORD is to be praised.
19½Ã 113:4 The LORD is high above all nations, and his glory above the heavens.
19½Ã 113:5 Who is like the LORD our God, who is seated on high,
19½Ã 113:6 who looks far down on the heavens and the earth?
19½Ã 113:7 He raises the poor from the dust, and lifts the needy from the ash heap,
19½Ã 113:8 to make them sit with princes, with the princes of his people.
19½Ã 113:9 He gives the barren woman a home, making her the joyous mother of children. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 114:1 When Israel went out from Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people of strange language,
19½Ã 114:2 Judah became God's sanctuary, Israel his dominion.
19½Ã 114:3 The sea looked and fled; Jordan turned back.
19½Ã 114:4 The mountains skipped like rams, the hills like lambs.
19½Ã 114:5 Why is it, O sea, that you flee? O Jordan, that you turn back?
19½Ã 114:6 O mountains, that you skip like rams? O hills, like lambs?
19½Ã 114:7 Tremble, O earth, at the presence of the LORD, at the presence of the God of Jacob,
19½Ã 114:8 who turns the rock into a pool of water, the flint into a spring of water.
19½Ã 115:1 Not to us, O LORD, not to us, but to your name give glory, for the sake of your steadfast love and your faithfulness.
19½Ã 115:2 Why should the nations say, "Where is their God?"
19½Ã 115:3 Our God is in the heavens; he does whatever he pleases.
19½Ã 115:4 Their idols are silver and gold, the work of human hands.
19½Ã 115:5 They have mouths, but do not speak; eyes, but do not see.
19½Ã 115:6 They have ears, but do not hear; noses, but do not smell.
19½Ã 115:7 They have hands, but do not feel; feet, but do not walk; they make no sound in their throats.
19½Ã 115:8 Those who make them are like them; so are all who trust in them.
19½Ã 115:9 O Israel, trust in the LORD! He is their help and their shield.
19½Ã 115:10 O house of Aaron, trust in the LORD! He is their help and their shield.
19½Ã 115:11 You who fear the LORD, trust in the LORD! He is their help and their shield.
19½Ã 115:12 The LORD has been mindful of us; he will bless us; he will bless the house of Israel; he will bless the house of Aaron;
19½Ã 115:13 he will bless those who fear the LORD, both small and great.
19½Ã 115:14 May the LORD give you increase, both you and your children.
19½Ã 115:15 May you be blessed by the LORD, who made heaven and earth.
19½Ã 115:16 The heavens are the LORD's heavens, but the earth he has given to human beings.
19½Ã 115:17 The dead do not praise the LORD, nor do any that go down into silence.
19½Ã 115:18 But we will bless the LORD from this time on and forevermore. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 116:1 I love the LORD, because he has heard my voice and my supplications.
19½Ã 116:2 Because he inclined his ear to me, therefore I will call on him as long as I live.
19½Ã 116:3 The snares of death encompassed me; the pangs of Sheol laid hold on me; I suffered distress and anguish.
19½Ã 116:4 Then I called on the name of the LORD: "O LORD, I pray, save my life!"
19½Ã 116:5 Gracious is the LORD, and righteous; our God is merciful.
19½Ã 116:6 The LORD protects the simple; when I was brought low, he saved me.
19½Ã 116:7 Return, O my soul, to your rest, for the LORD has dealt bountifully with you.
19½Ã 116:8 For you have delivered my soul from death, my eyes from tears, my feet from stumbling.
19½Ã 116:9 I walk before the LORD in the land of the living.
19½Ã 116:10 I kept my faith, even when I said, "I am greatly afflicted";
19½Ã 116:11 I said in my consternation, "Everyone is a liar."
19½Ã 116:12 What shall I return to the LORD for all his bounty to me?
19½Ã 116:13 I will lift up the cup of salvation and call on the name of the LORD,
19½Ã 116:14 I will pay my vows to the LORD in the presence of all his people.
19½Ã 116:15 Precious in the sight of the LORD is the death of his faithful ones.
19½Ã 116:16 O LORD, I am your servant; I am your servant, the child of your serving girl. You have loosed my bonds.
19½Ã 116:17 I will offer to you a thanksgiving sacrifice and call on the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 116:18 I will pay my vows to the LORD in the presence of all his people,
19½Ã 116:19 in the courts of the house of the LORD, in your midst, O Jerusalem. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 117:1 Praise the LORD, all you nations! Extol him, all you peoples!
19½Ã 117:2 For great is his steadfast love toward us, and the faithfulness of the LORD endures forever. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 118:1 O give thanks to the LORD, for he is good; his steadfast love endures forever!
19½Ã 118:2 Let Israel say, "His steadfast love endures forever."
19½Ã 118:3 Let the house of Aaron say, "His steadfast love endures forever."
19½Ã 118:4 Let those who fear the LORD say, "His steadfast love endures forever."
19½Ã 118:5 Out of my distress I called on the LORD; the LORD answered me and set me in a broad place.
19½Ã 118:6 With the LORD on my side I do not fear. What can mortals do to me?
19½Ã 118:7 The LORD is on my side to help me; I shall look in triumph on those who hate me.
19½Ã 118:8 It is better to take refuge in the LORD than to put confidence in mortals.
19½Ã 118:9 It is better to take refuge in the LORD than to put confidence in princes.
19½Ã 118:10 All nations surrounded me; in the name of the LORD I cut them off!
19½Ã 118:11 They surrounded me, surrounded me on every side; in the name of the LORD I cut them off!
19½Ã 118:12 They surrounded me like bees; they blazed like a fire of thorns; in the name of the LORD I cut them off!
19½Ã 118:13 I was pushed hard, so that I was falling, but the LORD helped me.
19½Ã 118:14 The LORD is my strength and my might; he has become my salvation.
19½Ã 118:15 There are glad songs of victory in the tents of the righteous: "The right hand of the LORD does valiantly;
19½Ã 118:16 the right hand of the LORD is exalted; the right hand of the LORD does valiantly."
19½Ã 118:17 I shall not die, but I shall live, and recount the deeds of the LORD.
19½Ã 118:18 The LORD has punished me severely, but he did not give me over to death.
19½Ã 118:19 Open to me the gates of righteousness, that I may enter through them and give thanks to the LORD.
19½Ã 118:20 This is the gate of the LORD; the righteous shall enter through it.
19½Ã 118:21 I thank you that you have answered me and have become my salvation.
19½Ã 118:22 The stone that the builders rejected has become the chief cornerstone.
19½Ã 118:23 This is the LORD's doing; it is marvelous in our eyes.
19½Ã 118:24 This is the day that the LORD has made; let us rejoice and be glad in it.
19½Ã 118:25 Save us, we beseech you, O LORD! O LORD, we beseech you, give us success!
19½Ã 118:26 Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the LORD. We bless you from the house of the LORD.
19½Ã 118:27 The LORD is God, and he has given us light. Bind the festal procession with branches, up to the horns of the altar.
19½Ã 118:28 You are my God, and I will give thanks to you; you are my God, I will extol you.
19½Ã 118:29 O give thanks to the LORD, for he is good, for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 119:1 Happy are those whose way is blameless, who walk in the law of the LORD.
19½Ã 119:2 Happy are those who keep his decrees, who seek him with their whole heart,
19½Ã 119:3 who also do no wrong, but walk in his ways.
19½Ã 119:4 You have commanded your precepts to be kept diligently.
19½Ã 119:5 O that my ways may be steadfast in keeping your statutes!
19½Ã 119:6 Then I shall not be put to shame, having my eyes fixed on all your commandments.
19½Ã 119:7 I will praise you with an upright heart, when I learn your righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:8 I will observe your statutes; do not utterly forsake me.
19½Ã 119:9 How can young people keep their way pure? By guarding it according to your word.
19½Ã 119:10 With my whole heart I seek you; do not let me stray from your commandments.
19½Ã 119:11 I treasure your word in my heart, so that I may not sin against you.
19½Ã 119:12 Blessed are you, O LORD; teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:13 With my lips I declare all the ordinances of your mouth.
19½Ã 119:14 I delight in the way of your decrees as much as in all riches.
19½Ã 119:15 I will meditate on your precepts, and fix my eyes on your ways.
19½Ã 119:16 I will delight in your statutes; I will not forget your word.
19½Ã 119:17 Deal bountifully with your servant, so that I may live and observe your word.
19½Ã 119:18 Open my eyes, so that I may behold wondrous things out of your law.
19½Ã 119:19 I live as an alien in the land; do not hide your commandments from me.
19½Ã 119:20 My soul is consumed with longing for your ordinances at all times.
19½Ã 119:21 You rebuke the insolent, accursed ones, who wander from your commandments;
19½Ã 119:22 take away from me their scorn and contempt, for I have kept your decrees.
19½Ã 119:23 Even though princes sit plotting against me, your servant will meditate on your statutes.
19½Ã 119:24 Your decrees are my delight, they are my counselors.
19½Ã 119:25 My soul clings to the dust; revive me according to your word.
19½Ã 119:26 When I told of my ways, you answered me; teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:27 Make me understand the way of your precepts, and I will meditate on your wondrous works.
19½Ã 119:28 My soul melts away for sorrow; strengthen me according to your word.
19½Ã 119:29 Put false ways far from me; and graciously teach me your law.
19½Ã 119:30 I have chosen the way of faithfulness; I set your ordinances before me.
19½Ã 119:31 I cling to your decrees, O LORD; let me not be put to shame.
19½Ã 119:32 I run the way of your commandments, for you enlarge my understanding.
19½Ã 119:33 Teach me, O LORD, the way of your statutes, and I will observe it to the end.
19½Ã 119:34 Give me understanding, that I may keep your law and observe it with my whole heart.
19½Ã 119:35 Lead me in the path of your commandments, for I delight in it.
19½Ã 119:36 Turn my heart to your decrees, and not to selfish gain.
19½Ã 119:37 Turn my eyes from looking at vanities; give me life in your ways.
19½Ã 119:38 Confirm to your servant your promise, which is for those who fear you.
19½Ã 119:39 Turn away the disgrace that I dread, for your ordinances are good.
19½Ã 119:40 See, I have longed for your precepts; in your righteousness give me life.
19½Ã 119:41 Let your steadfast love come to me, O LORD, your salvation according to your promise.
19½Ã 119:42 Then I shall have an answer for those who taunt me, for I trust in your word.
19½Ã 119:43 Do not take the word of truth utterly out of my mouth, for my hope is in your ordinances.
19½Ã 119:44 I will keep your law continually, forever and ever.
19½Ã 119:45 I shall walk at liberty, for I have sought your precepts.
19½Ã 119:46 I will also speak of your decrees before kings, and shall not be put to shame;
19½Ã 119:47 I find my delight in your commandments, because I love them.
19½Ã 119:48 I revere your commandments, which I love, and I will meditate on your statutes.
19½Ã 119:49 Remember your word to your servant, in which you have made me hope.
19½Ã 119:50 This is my comfort in my distress, that your promise gives me life.
19½Ã 119:51 The arrogant utterly deride me, but I do not turn away from your law.
19½Ã 119:52 When I think of your ordinances from of old, I take comfort, O LORD.
19½Ã 119:53 Hot indignation seizes me because of the wicked, those who forsake your law.
19½Ã 119:54 Your statutes have been my songs wherever I make my home.
19½Ã 119:55 I remember your name in the night, O LORD, and keep your law.
19½Ã 119:56 This blessing has fallen to me, for I have kept your precepts.
19½Ã 119:57 The LORD is my portion; I promise to keep your words.
19½Ã 119:58 I implore your favor with all my heart; be gracious to me according to your promise.
19½Ã 119:59 When I think of your ways, I turn my feet to your decrees;
19½Ã 119:60 I hurry and do not delay to keep your commandments.
19½Ã 119:61 Though the cords of the wicked ensnare me, I do not forget your law.
19½Ã 119:62 At midnight I rise to praise you, because of your righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:63 I am a companion of all who fear you, of those who keep your precepts.
19½Ã 119:64 The earth, O LORD, is full of your steadfast love; teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:65 You have dealt well with your servant, O LORD, according to your word.
19½Ã 119:66 Teach me good judgment and knowledge, for I believe in your commandments.
19½Ã 119:67 Before I was humbled I went astray, but now I keep your word.
19½Ã 119:68 You are good and do good; teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:69 The arrogant smear me with lies, but with my whole heart I keep your precepts.
19½Ã 119:70 Their hearts are fat and gross, but I delight in your law.
19½Ã 119:71 It is good for me that I was humbled, so that I might learn your statutes.
19½Ã 119:72 The law of your mouth is better to me than thousands of gold and silver pieces.
19½Ã 119:73 Your hands have made and fashioned me; give me understanding that I may learn your commandments.
19½Ã 119:74 Those who fear you shall see me and rejoice, because I have hoped in your word.
19½Ã 119:75 I know, O LORD, that your judgments are right, and that in faithfulness you have humbled me.
19½Ã 119:76 Let your steadfast love become my comfort according to your promise to your servant.
19½Ã 119:77 Let your mercy come to me, that I may live; for your law is my delight.
19½Ã 119:78 Let the arrogant be put to shame, because they have subverted me with guile; as for me, I will meditate on your precepts.
19½Ã 119:79 Let those who fear you turn to me, so that they may know your decrees.
19½Ã 119:80 May my heart be blameless in your statutes, so that I may not be put to shame.
19½Ã 119:81 My soul languishes for your salvation; I hope in your word.
19½Ã 119:82 My eyes fail with watching for your promise; I ask, "When will you comfort me?"
19½Ã 119:83 For I have become like a wineskin in the smoke, yet I have not forgotten your statutes.
19½Ã 119:84 How long must your servant endure? When will you judge those who persecute me?
19½Ã 119:85 The arrogant have dug pitfalls for me; they flout your law.
19½Ã 119:86 All your commandments are enduring; I am persecuted without cause; help me!
19½Ã 119:87 They have almost made an end of me on earth; but I have not forsaken your precepts.
19½Ã 119:88 In your steadfast love spare my life, so that I may keep the decrees of your mouth.
19½Ã 119:89 The LORD exists forever; your word is firmly fixed in heaven.
19½Ã 119:90 Your faithfulness endures to all generations; you have established the earth, and it stands fast.
19½Ã 119:91 By your appointment they stand today, for all things are your servants.
19½Ã 119:92 If your law had not been my delight, I would have perished in my misery.
19½Ã 119:93 I will never forget your precepts, for by them you have given me life.
19½Ã 119:94 I am yours; save me, for I have sought your precepts.
19½Ã 119:95 The wicked lie in wait to destroy me, but I consider your decrees.
19½Ã 119:96 I have seen a limit to all perfection, but your commandment is exceedingly broad.
19½Ã 119:97 Oh, how I love your law! It is my meditation all day long.
19½Ã 119:98 Your commandment makes me wiser than my enemies, for it is always with me.
19½Ã 119:99 I have more understanding than all my teachers, for your decrees are my meditation.
19½Ã 119:100 I understand more than the aged, for I keep your precepts.
19½Ã 119:101 I hold back my feet from every evil way, in order to keep your word.
19½Ã 119:102 I do not turn away from your ordinances, for you have taught me.
19½Ã 119:103 How sweet are your words to my taste, sweeter than honey to my mouth!
19½Ã 119:104 Through your precepts I get understanding; therefore I hate every false way.
19½Ã 119:105 Your word is a lamp to my feet and a light to my path.
19½Ã 119:106 I have sworn an oath and confirmed it, to observe your righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:107 I am severely afflicted; give me life, O LORD, according to your word.
19½Ã 119:108 Accept my offerings of praise, O LORD, and teach me your ordinances.
19½Ã 119:109 I hold my life in my hand continually, but I do not forget your law.
19½Ã 119:110 The wicked have laid a snare for me, but I do not stray from your precepts.
19½Ã 119:111 Your decrees are my heritage forever; they are the joy of my heart.
19½Ã 119:112 I incline my heart to perform your statutes forever, to the end.
19½Ã 119:113 I hate the double-minded, but I love your law.
19½Ã 119:114 You are my hiding place and my shield; I hope in your word.
19½Ã 119:115 Go away from me, you evildoers, that I may keep the commandments of my God.
19½Ã 119:116 Uphold me according to your promise, that I may live, and let me not be put to shame in my hope.
19½Ã 119:117 Hold me up, that I may be safe and have regard for your statutes continually.
19½Ã 119:118 You spurn all who go astray from your statutes; for their cunning is in vain.
19½Ã 119:119 All the wicked of the earth you count as dross; therefore I love your decrees.
19½Ã 119:120 My flesh trembles for fear of you, and I am afraid of your judgments.
19½Ã 119:121 I have done what is just and right; do not leave me to my oppressors.
19½Ã 119:122 Guarantee your servant's well-being; do not let the godless oppress me.
19½Ã 119:123 My eyes fail from watching for your salvation, and for the fulfillment of your righteous promise.
19½Ã 119:124 Deal with your servant according to your steadfast love, and teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:125 I am your servant; give me understanding, so that I may know your decrees.
19½Ã 119:126 It is time for the LORD to act, for your law has been broken.
19½Ã 119:127 Truly I love your commandments more than gold, more than fine gold.
19½Ã 119:128 Truly I direct my steps by all your precepts; I hate every false way.
19½Ã 119:129 Your decrees are wonderful; therefore my soul keeps them.
19½Ã 119:130 The unfolding of your words gives light; it imparts understanding to the simple.
19½Ã 119:131 With open mouth I pant, because I long for your commandments.
19½Ã 119:132 Turn to me and be gracious to me, as is your custom toward those who love your name.
19½Ã 119:133 Keep my steps steady according to your promise, and never let iniquity have dominion over me.
19½Ã 119:134 Redeem me from human oppression, that I may keep your precepts.
19½Ã 119:135 Make your face shine upon your servant, and teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:136 My eyes shed streams of tears because your law is not kept.
19½Ã 119:137 You are righteous, O LORD, and your judgments are right.
19½Ã 119:138 You have appointed your decrees in righteousness and in all faithfulness.
19½Ã 119:139 My zeal consumes me because my foes forget your words.
19½Ã 119:140 Your promise is well tried, and your servant loves it.
19½Ã 119:141 I am small and despised, yet I do not forget your precepts.
19½Ã 119:142 Your righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and your law is the truth.
19½Ã 119:143 Trouble and anguish have come upon me, but your commandments are my delight.
19½Ã 119:144 Your decrees are righteous forever; give me understanding that I may live.
19½Ã 119:145 With my whole heart I cry; answer me, O LORD. I will keep your statutes.
19½Ã 119:146 I cry to you; save me, that I may observe your decrees.
19½Ã 119:147 I rise before dawn and cry for help; I put my hope in your words.
19½Ã 119:148 My eyes are awake before each watch of the night, that I may meditate on your promise.
19½Ã 119:149 In your steadfast love hear my voice; O LORD, in your justice preserve my life.
19½Ã 119:150 Those who persecute me with evil purpose draw near; they are far from your law.
19½Ã 119:151 Yet you are near, O LORD, and all your commandments are true.
19½Ã 119:152 Long ago I learned from your decrees that you have established them forever.
19½Ã 119:153 Look on my misery and rescue me, for I do not forget your law.
19½Ã 119:154 Plead my cause and redeem me; give me life according to your promise.
19½Ã 119:155 Salvation is far from the wicked, for they do not seek your statutes.
19½Ã 119:156 Great is your mercy, O LORD; give me life according to your justice.
19½Ã 119:157 Many are my persecutors and my adversaries, yet I do not swerve from your decrees.
19½Ã 119:158 I look at the faithless with disgust, because they do not keep your commands.
19½Ã 119:159 Consider how I love your precepts; preserve my life according to your steadfast love.
19½Ã 119:160 The sum of your word is truth; and every one of your righteous ordinances endures forever.
19½Ã 119:161 Princes persecute me without cause, but my heart stands in awe of your words.
19½Ã 119:162 I rejoice at your word like one who finds great spoil.
19½Ã 119:163 I hate and abhor falsehood, but I love your law.
19½Ã 119:164 Seven times a day I praise you for your righteous ordinances.
19½Ã 119:165 Great peace have those who love your law; nothing can make them stumble.
19½Ã 119:166 I hope for your salvation, O LORD, and I fulfill your commandments.
19½Ã 119:167 My soul keeps your decrees; I love them exceedingly.
19½Ã 119:168 I keep your precepts and decrees, for all my ways are before you.
19½Ã 119:169 Let my cry come before you, O LORD; give me understanding according to your word.
19½Ã 119:170 Let my supplication come before you; deliver me according to your promise.
19½Ã 119:171 My lips will pour forth praise, because you teach me your statutes.
19½Ã 119:172 My tongue will sing of your promise, for all your commandments are right.
19½Ã 119:173 Let your hand be ready to help me, for I have chosen your precepts.
19½Ã 119:174 I long for your salvation, O LORD, and your law is my delight.
19½Ã 119:175 Let me live that I may praise you, and let your ordinances help me.
19½Ã 119:176 I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek out your servant, for I do not forget your commandments.
19½Ã 120:1 A Song of Ascents. In my distress I cry to the LORD, that he may answer me:
19½Ã 120:2 "Deliver me, O LORD, from lying lips, from a deceitful tongue."
19½Ã 120:3 What shall be given to you? And what more shall be done to you, you deceitful tongue?
19½Ã 120:4 A warrior's sharp arrows, with glowing coals of the broom tree!
19½Ã 120:5 Woe is me, that I am an alien in Meshech, that I must live among the tents of Kedar.
19½Ã 120:6 Too long have I had my dwelling among those who hate peace.
19½Ã 120:7 I am for peace; but when I speak, they are for war.
19½Ã 121:1 A Song of Ascents. I lift up my eyes to the hills--from where will my help come?
19½Ã 121:2 My help comes from the LORD, who made heaven and earth.
19½Ã 121:3 He will not let your foot be moved; he who keeps you will not slumber.
19½Ã 121:4 He who keeps Israel will neither slumber nor sleep.
19½Ã 121:5 The LORD is your keeper; the LORD is your shade at your right hand.
19½Ã 121:6 The sun shall not strike you by day, nor the moon by night.
19½Ã 121:7 The LORD will keep you from all evil; he will keep your life.
19½Ã 121:8 The LORD will keep your going out and your coming in from this time on and forevermore.
19½Ã 122:1 A Song of Ascents. Of David. I was glad when they said to me, "Let us go to the house of the LORD!"
19½Ã 122:2 Our feet are standing within your gates, O Jerusalem.
19½Ã 122:3 Jerusalem--built as a city that is bound firmly together.
19½Ã 122:4 To it the tribes go up, the tribes of the LORD, as was decreed for Israel, to give thanks to the name of the LORD.
19½Ã 122:5 For there the thrones for judgment were set up, the thrones of the house of David.
19½Ã 122:6 Pray for the peace of Jerusalem: "May they prosper who love you.
19½Ã 122:7 Peace be within your walls, and security within your towers."
19½Ã 122:8 For the sake of my relatives and friends I will say, "Peace be within you."
19½Ã 122:9 For the sake of the house of the LORD our God, I will seek your good.
19½Ã 123:1 A Song of Ascents. To you I lift up my eyes, O you who are enthroned in the heavens!
19½Ã 123:2 As the eyes of servants look to the hand of their master, as the eyes of a maid to the hand of her mistress, so our eyes look to the LORD our God, until he has mercy upon us.
19½Ã 123:3 Have mercy upon us, O LORD, have mercy upon us, for we have had more than enough of contempt.
19½Ã 123:4 Our soul has had more than its fill of the scorn of those who are at ease, of the contempt of the proud.
19½Ã 124:1 A Song of Ascents. Of David. If it had not been the LORD who was on our side--let Israel now say--
19½Ã 124:2 if it had not been the LORD who was on our side, when our enemies attacked us,
19½Ã 124:3 then they would have swallowed us up alive, when their anger was kindled against us;
19½Ã 124:4 then the flood would have swept us away, the torrent would have gone over us;
19½Ã 124:5 then over us would have gone the raging waters.
19½Ã 124:6 Blessed be the LORD, who has not given us as prey to their teeth.
19½Ã 124:7 We have escaped like a bird from the snare of the fowlers; the snare is broken, and we have escaped.
19½Ã 124:8 Our help is in the name of the LORD, who made heaven and earth.
19½Ã 125:1 A Song of Ascents. Those who trust in the LORD are like Mount Zion, which cannot be moved, but abides forever.
19½Ã 125:2 As the mountains surround Jerusalem, so the LORD surrounds his people, from this time on and forevermore.
19½Ã 125:3 For the scepter of wickedness shall not rest on the land allotted to the righteous, so that the righteous might not stretch out their hands to do wrong.
19½Ã 125:4 Do good, O LORD, to those who are good, and to those who are upright in their hearts.
19½Ã 125:5 But those who turn aside to their own crooked ways the LORD will lead away with evildoers. Peace be upon Israel!
19½Ã 126:1 A Song of Ascents. When the LORD restored the fortunes of Zion, we were like those who dream.
19½Ã 126:2 Then our mouth was filled with laughter, and our tongue with shouts of joy; then it was said among the nations, "The LORD has done great things for them."
19½Ã 126:3 The LORD has done great things for us, and we rejoiced.
19½Ã 126:4 Restore our fortunes, O LORD, like the watercourses in the Negeb.
19½Ã 126:5 May those who sow in tears reap with shouts of joy.
19½Ã 126:6 Those who go out weeping, bearing the seed for sowing, shall come home with shouts of joy, carrying their sheaves.
19½Ã 127:1 A Song of Ascents. Of Solomon. Unless the LORD builds the house, those who build it labor in vain. Unless the LORD guards the city, the guard keeps watch in vain.
19½Ã 127:2 It is in vain that you rise up early and go late to rest, eating the bread of anxious toil; for he gives sleep to his beloved.
19½Ã 127:3 Sons are indeed a heritage from the LORD, the fruit of the womb a reward.
19½Ã 127:4 Like arrows in the hand of a warrior are the sons of one's youth.
19½Ã 127:5 Happy is the man who has his quiver full of them. He shall not be put to shame when he speaks with his enemies in the gate.
19½Ã 128:1 A Song of Ascents. Happy is everyone who fears the LORD, who walks in his ways.
19½Ã 128:2 You shall eat the fruit of the labor of your hands; you shall be happy, and it shall go well with you.
19½Ã 128:3 Your wife will be like a fruitful vine within your house; your children will be like olive shoots around your table.
19½Ã 128:4 Thus shall the man be blessed who fears the LORD.
19½Ã 128:5 The LORD bless you from Zion. May you see the prosperity of Jerusalem all the days of your life.
19½Ã 128:6 May you see your children's children. Peace be upon Israel!
19½Ã 129:1 A Song of Ascents. "Often have they attacked me from my youth" --let Israel now say--
19½Ã 129:2 "often have they attacked me from my youth, yet they have not prevailed against me.
19½Ã 129:3 The plowers plowed on my back; they made their furrows long."
19½Ã 129:4 The LORD is righteous; he has cut the cords of the wicked.
19½Ã 129:5 May all who hate Zion be put to shame and turned backward.
19½Ã 129:6 Let them be like the grass on the housetops that withers before it grows up,
19½Ã 129:7 with which reapers do not fill their hands or binders of sheaves their arms,
19½Ã 129:8 while those who pass by do not say, "The blessing of the LORD be upon you! We bless you in the name of the LORD!"
19½Ã 130:1 A Song of Ascents. Out of the depths I cry to you, O LORD.
19½Ã 130:2 Lord, hear my voice! Let your ears be attentive to the voice of my supplications!
19½Ã 130:3 If you, O LORD, should mark iniquities, Lord, who could stand?
19½Ã 130:4 But there is forgiveness with you, so that you may be revered.
19½Ã 130:5 I wait for the LORD, my soul waits, and in his word I hope;
19½Ã 130:6 my soul waits for the Lord more than those who watch for the morning, more than those who watch for the morning.
19½Ã 130:7 O Israel, hope in the LORD! For with the LORD there is steadfast love, and with him is great power to redeem.
19½Ã 130:8 It is he who will redeem Israel from all its iniquities.
19½Ã 131:1 A Song of Ascents. Of David. O LORD, my heart is not lifted up, my eyes are not raised too high; I do not occupy myself with things too great and too marvelous for me.
19½Ã 131:2 But I have calmed and quieted my soul, like a weaned child with its mother; my soul is like the weaned child that is with me.
19½Ã 131:3 O Israel, hope in the LORD from this time on and forevermore.
19½Ã 132:1 A Song of Ascents. O LORD, remember in David's favor all the hardships he endured;
19½Ã 132:2 how he swore to the LORD and vowed to the Mighty One of Jacob,
19½Ã 132:3 "I will not enter my house or get into my bed;
19½Ã 132:4 I will not give sleep to my eyes or slumber to my eyelids,
19½Ã 132:5 until I find a place for the LORD, a dwelling place for the Mighty One of Jacob."
19½Ã 132:6 We heard of it in Ephrathah; we found it in the fields of Jaar.
19½Ã 132:7 "Let us go to his dwelling place; let us worship at his footstool."
19½Ã 132:8 Rise up, O LORD, and go to your resting place, you and the ark of your might.
19½Ã 132:9 Let your priests be clothed with righteousness, and let your faithful shout for joy.
19½Ã 132:10 For your servant David's sake do not turn away the face of your anointed one.
19½Ã 132:11 The LORD swore to David a sure oath from which he will not turn back: "One of the sons of your body I will set on your throne.
19½Ã 132:12 If your sons keep my covenant and my decrees that I shall teach them, their sons also, forevermore, shall sit on your throne."
19½Ã 132:13 For the LORD has chosen Zion; he has desired it for his habitation:
19½Ã 132:14 "This is my resting place forever; here I will reside, for I have desired it.
19½Ã 132:15 I will abundantly bless its provisions; I will satisfy its poor with bread.
19½Ã 132:16 Its priests I will clothe with salvation, and its faithful will shout for joy.
19½Ã 132:17 There I will cause a horn to sprout up for David; I have prepared a lamp for my anointed one.
19½Ã 132:18 His enemies I will clothe with disgrace, but on him, his crown will gleam."
19½Ã 133:1 A Song of Ascents. How very good and pleasant it is when kindred live together in unity!
19½Ã 133:2 It is like the precious oil on the head, running down upon the beard, on the beard of Aaron, running down over the collar of his robes.
19½Ã 133:3 It is like the dew of Hermon, which falls on the mountains of Zion. For there the LORD ordained his blessing, life forevermore.
19½Ã 134:1 A Song of Ascents. Come, bless the LORD, all you servants of the LORD, who stand by night in the house of the LORD!
19½Ã 134:2 Lift up your hands to the holy place, and bless the LORD.
19½Ã 134:3 May the LORD, maker of heaven and earth, bless you from Zion.
19½Ã 135:1 Praise the LORD! Praise the name of the LORD; give praise, O servants of the LORD,
19½Ã 135:2 you that stand in the house of the LORD, in the courts of the house of our God.
19½Ã 135:3 Praise the LORD, for the LORD is good; sing to his name, for he is gracious.
19½Ã 135:4 For the LORD has chosen Jacob for himself, Israel as his own possession.
19½Ã 135:5 For I know that the LORD is great; our Lord is above all gods.
19½Ã 135:6 Whatever the LORD pleases he does, in heaven and on earth, in the seas and all deeps.
19½Ã 135:7 He it is who makes the clouds rise at the end of the earth; he makes lightnings for the rain and brings out the wind from his storehouses.
19½Ã 135:8 He it was who struck down the firstborn of Egypt, both human beings and animals;
19½Ã 135:9 he sent signs and wonders into your midst, O Egypt, against Pharaoh and all his servants.
19½Ã 135:10 He struck down many nations and killed mighty kings--
19½Ã 135:11 Sihon, king of the Amorites, and Og, king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan--
19½Ã 135:12 and gave their land as a heritage, a heritage to his people Israel.
19½Ã 135:13 Your name, O LORD, endures forever, your renown, O LORD, throughout all ages.
19½Ã 135:14 For the LORD will vindicate his people, and have compassion on his servants.
19½Ã 135:15 The idols of the nations are silver and gold, the work of human hands.
19½Ã 135:16 They have mouths, but they do not speak; they have eyes, but they do not see;
19½Ã 135:17 they have ears, but they do not hear, and there is no breath in their mouths.
19½Ã 135:18 Those who make them and all who trust them shall become like them.
19½Ã 135:19 O house of Israel, bless the LORD! O house of Aaron, bless the LORD!
19½Ã 135:20 O house of Levi, bless the LORD! You that fear the LORD, bless the LORD!
19½Ã 135:21 Blessed be the LORD from Zion, he who resides in Jerusalem. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 136:1 O give thanks to the LORD, for he is good, for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 136:2 O give thanks to the God of gods, for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 136:3 O give thanks to the Lord of lords, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:4 who alone does great wonders, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:5 who by understanding made the heavens, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:6 who spread out the earth on the waters, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:7 who made the great lights, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:8 the sun to rule over the day, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:9 the moon and stars to rule over the night, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:10 who struck Egypt through their firstborn, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:11 and brought Israel out from among them, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:12 with a strong hand and an outstretched arm, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:13 who divided the Red Sea in two, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:14 and made Israel pass through the midst of it, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:15 but overthrew Pharaoh and his army in the Red Sea, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:16 who led his people through the wilderness, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:17 who struck down great kings, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:18 and killed famous kings, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:19 Sihon, king of the Amorites, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:20 and Og, king of Bashan, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:21 and gave their land as a heritage, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:22 a heritage to his servant Israel, for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 136:23 It is he who remembered us in our low estate, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:24 and rescued us from our foes, for his steadfast love endures forever;
19½Ã 136:25 who gives food to all flesh, for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 136:26 O give thanks to the God of heaven, for his steadfast love endures forever.
19½Ã 137:1 By the rivers of Babylon--there we sat down and there we wept when we remembered Zion.
19½Ã 137:2 On the willows there we hung up our harps.
19½Ã 137:3 For there our captors asked us for songs, and our tormentors asked for mirth, saying, "Sing us one of the songs of Zion!"
19½Ã 137:4 How could we sing the LORD's song in a foreign land?
19½Ã 137:5 If I forget you, O Jerusalem, let my right hand wither!
19½Ã 137:6 Let my tongue cling to the roof of my mouth, if I do not remember you, if I do not set Jerusalem above my highest joy.
19½Ã 137:7 Remember, O LORD, against the Edomites the day of Jerusalem's fall, how they said, "Tear it down! Tear it down! Down to its foundations!"
19½Ã 137:8 O daughter Babylon, you devastator! Happy shall they be who pay you back what you have done to us!
19½Ã 137:9 Happy shall they be who take your little ones and dash them against the rock!
19½Ã 138:1 Of David. I give you thanks, O LORD, with my whole heart; before the gods I sing your praise;
19½Ã 138:2 I bow down toward your holy temple and give thanks to your name for your steadfast love and your faithfulness; for you have exalted your name and your word above everything.
19½Ã 138:3 On the day I called, you answered me, you increased my strength of soul.
19½Ã 138:4 All the kings of the earth shall praise you, O LORD, for they have heard the words of your mouth.
19½Ã 138:5 They shall sing of the ways of the LORD, for great is the glory of the LORD.
19½Ã 138:6 For though the LORD is high, he regards the lowly; but the haughty he perceives from far away.
19½Ã 138:7 Though I walk in the midst of trouble, you preserve me against the wrath of my enemies; you stretch out your hand, and your right hand delivers me.
19½Ã 138:8 The LORD will fulfill his purpose for me; your steadfast love, O LORD, endures forever. Do not forsake the work of your hands.
19½Ã 139:1 To the leader. Of David. A Psalm. O LORD, you have searched me and known me.
19½Ã 139:2 You know when I sit down and when I rise up; you discern my thoughts from far away.
19½Ã 139:3 You search out my path and my lying down, and are acquainted with all my ways.
19½Ã 139:4 Even before a word is on my tongue, O LORD, you know it completely.
19½Ã 139:5 You hem me in, behind and before, and lay your hand upon me.
19½Ã 139:6 Such knowledge is too wonderful for me; it is so high that I cannot attain it.
19½Ã 139:7 Where can I go from your spirit? Or where can I flee from your presence?
19½Ã 139:8 If I ascend to heaven, you are there; if I make my bed in Sheol, you are there.
19½Ã 139:9 If I take the wings of the morning and settle at the farthest limits of the sea,
19½Ã 139:10 even there your hand shall lead me, and your right hand shall hold me fast.
19½Ã 139:11 If I say, "Surely the darkness shall cover me, and the light around me become night,"
19½Ã 139:12 even the darkness is not dark to you; the night is as bright as the day, for darkness is as light to you.
19½Ã 139:13 For it was you who formed my inward parts; you knit me together in my mother's womb.
19½Ã 139:14 I praise you, for I am fearfully and wonderfully made. Wonderful are your works; that I know very well.
19½Ã 139:15 My frame was not hidden from you, when I was being made in secret, intricately woven in the depths of the earth.
19½Ã 139:16 Your eyes beheld my unformed substance. In your book were written all the days that were formed for me, when none of them as yet existed.
19½Ã 139:17 How weighty to me are your thoughts, O God! How vast is the sum of them!
19½Ã 139:18 I try to count them--they are more than the sand; I come to the end--I am still with you.
19½Ã 139:19 O that you would kill the wicked, O God, and that the bloodthirsty would depart from me--
19½Ã 139:20 those who speak of you maliciously, and lift themselves up against you for evil!
19½Ã 139:21 Do I not hate those who hate you, O LORD? And do I not loathe those who rise up against you?
19½Ã 139:22 I hate them with perfect hatred; I count them my enemies.
19½Ã 139:23 Search me, O God, and know my heart; test me and know my thoughts.
19½Ã 139:24 See if there is any wicked way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.
19½Ã 140:1 To the leader. A Psalm of David. Deliver me, O LORD, from evildoers; protect me from those who are violent,
19½Ã 140:2 who plan evil things in their minds and stir up wars continually.
19½Ã 140:3 They make their tongue sharp as a snake's, and under their lips is the venom of vipers. Selah
19½Ã 140:4 Guard me, O LORD, from the hands of the wicked; protect me from the violent who have planned my downfall.
19½Ã 140:5 The arrogant have hidden a trap for me, and with cords they have spread a net, along the road they have set snares for me. Selah
19½Ã 140:6 I say to the LORD, "You are my God; give ear, O LORD, to the voice of my supplications."
19½Ã 140:7 O LORD, my Lord, my strong deliverer, you have covered my head in the day of battle.
19½Ã 140:8 Do not grant, O LORD, the desires of the wicked; do not further their evil plot. Selah
19½Ã 140:9 Those who surround me lift up their heads; let the mischief of their lips overwhelm them!
19½Ã 140:10 Let burning coals fall on them! Let them be flung into pits, no more to rise!
19½Ã 140:11 Do not let the slanderer be established in the land; let evil speedily hunt down the violent!
19½Ã 140:12 I know that the LORD maintains the cause of the needy, and executes justice for the poor.
19½Ã 140:13 Surely the righteous shall give thanks to your name; the upright shall live in your presence.
19½Ã 141:1 A Psalm of David. I call upon you, O LORD; come quickly to me; give ear to my voice when I call to you.
19½Ã 141:2 Let my prayer be counted as incense before you, and the lifting up of my hands as an evening sacrifice.
19½Ã 141:3 Set a guard over my mouth, O LORD; keep watch over the door of my lips.
19½Ã 141:4 Do not turn my heart to any evil, to busy myself with wicked deeds in company with those who work iniquity; do not let me eat of their delicacies.
19½Ã 141:5 Let the righteous strike me; let the faithful correct me. Never let the oil of the wicked anoint my head, for my prayer is continually against their wicked deeds.
19½Ã 141:6 When they are given over to those who shall condemn them, then they shall learn that my words were pleasant.
19½Ã 141:7 Like a rock that one breaks apart and shatters on the land, so shall their bones be strewn at the mouth of Sheol.
19½Ã 141:8 But my eyes are turned toward you, O GOD, my Lord; in you I seek refuge; do not leave me defenseless.
19½Ã 141:9 Keep me from the trap that they have laid for me, and from the snares of evildoers.
19½Ã 141:10 Let the wicked fall into their own nets, while I alone escape.
19½Ã 142:1 A Maskil of David. When he was in the cave. A Prayer. With my voice I cry to the LORD; with my voice I make supplication to the LORD.
19½Ã 142:2 I pour out my complaint before him; I tell my trouble before him.
19½Ã 142:3 When my spirit is faint, you know my way. In the path where I walk they have hidden a trap for me.
19½Ã 142:4 Look on my right hand and see--there is no one who takes notice of me; no refuge remains to me; no one cares for me.
19½Ã 142:5 I cry to you, O LORD; I say, "You are my refuge, my portion in the land of the living."
19½Ã 142:6 Give heed to my cry, for I am brought very low. Save me from my persecutors, for they are too strong for me.
19½Ã 142:7 Bring me out of prison, so that I may give thanks to your name. The righteous will surround me, for you will deal bountifully with me.
19½Ã 143:1 A Psalm of David. Hear my prayer, O LORD; give ear to my supplications in your faithfulness; answer me in your righteousness.
19½Ã 143:2 Do not enter into judgment with your servant, for no one living is righteous before you.
19½Ã 143:3 For the enemy has pursued me, crushing my life to the ground, making me sit in darkness like those long dead.
19½Ã 143:4 Therefore my spirit faints within me; my heart within me is appalled.
19½Ã 143:5 I remember the days of old, I think about all your deeds, I meditate on the works of your hands.
19½Ã 143:6 I stretch out my hands to you; my soul thirsts for you like a parched land. Selah
19½Ã 143:7 Answer me quickly, O LORD; my spirit fails. Do not hide your face from me, or I shall be like those who go down to the Pit.
19½Ã 143:8 Let me hear of your steadfast love in the morning, for in you I put my trust. Teach me the way I should go, for to you I lift up my soul.
19½Ã 143:9 Save me, O LORD, from my enemies; I have fled to you for refuge.
19½Ã 143:10 Teach me to do your will, for you are my God. Let your good spirit lead me on a level path.
19½Ã 143:11 For your name's sake, O LORD, preserve my life. In your righteousness bring me out of trouble.
19½Ã 143:12 In your steadfast love cut off my enemies, and destroy all my adversaries, for I am your servant.
19½Ã 144:1 Of David. Blessed be the LORD, my rock, who trains my hands for war, and my fingers for battle;
19½Ã 144:2 my rock and my fortress, my stronghold and my deliverer, my shield, in whom I take refuge, who subdues the peoples under me.
19½Ã 144:3 O LORD, what are human beings that you regard them, or mortals that you think of them?
19½Ã 144:4 They are like a breath; their days are like a passing shadow.
19½Ã 144:5 Bow your heavens, O LORD, and come down; touch the mountains so that they smoke.
19½Ã 144:6 Make the lightning flash and scatter them; send out your arrows and rout them.
19½Ã 144:7 Stretch out your hand from on high; set me free and rescue me from the mighty waters, from the hand of aliens,
19½Ã 144:8 whose mouths speak lies, and whose right hands are false.
19½Ã 144:9 I will sing a new song to you, O God; upon a ten-stringed harp I will play to you,
19½Ã 144:10 the one who gives victory to kings, who rescues his servant David.
19½Ã 144:11 Rescue me from the cruel sword, and deliver me from the hand of aliens, whose mouths speak lies, and whose right hands are false.
19½Ã 144:12 May our sons in their youth be like plants full grown, our daughters like corner pillars, cut for the building of a palace.
19½Ã 144:13 May our barns be filled, with produce of every kind; may our sheep increase by thousands, by tens of thousands in our fields,
19½Ã 144:14 and may our cattle be heavy with young. May there be no breach in the walls, no exile, and no cry of distress in our streets.
19½Ã 144:15 Happy are the people to whom such blessings fall; happy are the people whose God is the LORD.
19½Ã 145:1 Praise. Of David. I will extol you, my God and King, and bless your name forever and ever.
19½Ã 145:2 Every day I will bless you, and praise your name forever and ever.
19½Ã 145:3 Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised; his greatness is unsearchable.
19½Ã 145:4 One generation shall laud your works to another, and shall declare your mighty acts.
19½Ã 145:5 On the glorious splendor of your majesty, and on your wondrous works, I will meditate.
19½Ã 145:6 The might of your awesome deeds shall be proclaimed, and I will declare your greatness.
19½Ã 145:7 They shall celebrate the fame of your abundant goodness, and shall sing aloud of your righteousness.
19½Ã 145:8 The LORD is gracious and merciful, slow to anger and abounding in steadfast love.
19½Ã 145:9 The LORD is good to all, and his compassion is over all that he has made.
19½Ã 145:10 All your works shall give thanks to you, O LORD, and all your faithful shall bless you.
19½Ã 145:11 They shall speak of the glory of your kingdom, and tell of your power,
19½Ã 145:12 to make known to all people your mighty deeds, and the glorious splendor of your kingdom.
19½Ã 145:13 Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and your dominion endures throughout all generations. The LORD is faithful in all his words, and gracious in all his deeds.
19½Ã 145:14 The LORD upholds all who are falling, and raises up all who are bowed down.
19½Ã 145:15 The eyes of all look to you, and you give them their food in due season.
19½Ã 145:16 You open your hand, satisfying the desire of every living thing.
19½Ã 145:17 The LORD is just in all his ways, and kind in all his doings.
19½Ã 145:18 The LORD is near to all who call on him, to all who call on him in truth.
19½Ã 145:19 He fulfills the desire of all who fear him; he also hears their cry, and saves them.
19½Ã 145:20 The LORD watches over all who love him, but all the wicked he will destroy.
19½Ã 145:21 My mouth will speak the praise of the LORD, and all flesh will bless his holy name forever and ever.
19½Ã 146:1 Praise the LORD! Praise the LORD, O my soul!
19½Ã 146:2 I will praise the LORD as long as I live; I will sing praises to my God all my life long.
19½Ã 146:3 Do not put your trust in princes, in mortals, in whom there is no help.
19½Ã 146:4 When their breath departs, they return to the earth; on that very day their plans perish.
19½Ã 146:5 Happy are those whose help is the God of Jacob, whose hope is in the LORD their God,
19½Ã 146:6 who made heaven and earth, the sea, and all that is in them; who keeps faith forever;
19½Ã 146:7 who executes justice for the oppressed; who gives food to the hungry. The LORD sets the prisoners free;
19½Ã 146:8 the LORD opens the eyes of the blind. The LORD lifts up those who are bowed down; the LORD loves the righteous.
19½Ã 146:9 The LORD watches over the strangers; he upholds the orphan and the widow, but the way of the wicked he brings to ruin.
19½Ã 146:10 The LORD will reign forever, your God, O Zion, for all generations. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 147:1 Praise the LORD! How good it is to sing praises to our God; for he is gracious, and a song of praise is fitting.
19½Ã 147:2 The LORD builds up Jerusalem; he gathers the outcasts of Israel.
19½Ã 147:3 He heals the brokenhearted, and binds up their wounds.
19½Ã 147:4 He determines the number of the stars; he gives to all of them their names.
19½Ã 147:5 Great is our Lord, and abundant in power; his understanding is beyond measure.
19½Ã 147:6 The LORD lifts up the downtrodden; he casts the wicked to the ground.
19½Ã 147:7 Sing to the LORD with thanksgiving; make melody to our God on the lyre.
19½Ã 147:8 He covers the heavens with clouds, prepares rain for the earth, makes grass grow on the hills.
19½Ã 147:9 He gives to the animals their food, and to the young ravens when they cry.
19½Ã 147:10 His delight is not in the strength of the horse, nor his pleasure in the speed of a runner;
19½Ã 147:11 but the LORD takes pleasure in those who fear him, in those who hope in his steadfast love.
19½Ã 147:12 Praise the LORD, O Jerusalem! Praise your God, O Zion!
19½Ã 147:13 For he strengthens the bars of your gates; he blesses your children within you.
19½Ã 147:14 He grants peace within your borders; he fills you with the finest of wheat.
19½Ã 147:15 He sends out his command to the earth; his word runs swiftly.
19½Ã 147:16 He gives snow like wool; he scatters frost like ashes.
19½Ã 147:17 He hurls down hail like crumbs--who can stand before his cold?
19½Ã 147:18 He sends out his word, and melts them; he makes his wind blow, and the waters flow.
19½Ã 147:19 He declares his word to Jacob, his statutes and ordinances to Israel.
19½Ã 147:20 He has not dealt thus with any other nation; they do not know his ordinances. Praise the LORD!
19½Ã 148:1 Praise the LORD! Praise the LORD from the heavens; praise him in the heights!
19½Ã 148:2 Praise him, all his angels; praise him, all his host!
19½Ã 148:3 Praise him, sun and moon; praise him, all you shining stars!
19½Ã 148:4 Praise him, you highest heavens, and you waters above the heavens!
19½Ã 148:5 Let them praise the name of the LORD, for he commanded and they were created.
19½Ã 148:6 He established them forever and ever; he fixed their bounds, which cannot be passed.
